Headline: : Ford Teams Up With Microsoft to Deliver Sync; In-Car Digital System Exclusive to Ford
Story: * Ford Sync(TM), powered by Microsoft Auto software, is Ford's new fully integrated, voice-activated in-car communications and entertainment system for mobile phones and digital music players. * Sync will be available in 12 Ford, Lincoln and Mercury products beginning this calendar year. * Sync is the newest technology to emerge from the Ford-Microsoft relationship. * Users can access their mobile phone or digital music player - including genre, album, artist and song title - via voice commands. * Names and numbers in a mobile phone's address book are wirelessly and automatically transferred to the vehicle. * Sync can host nearly any digital media player, including the Apple iPod(R), Microsoft Zune, PlaysForSure players and most USB storage devices.       DETROIT, Jan. 7 /PRNewswire-FirstCall/ -- Ford Motor Company today announced the launch of a new factory-installed, in-car communications and entertainment system that is designed to change the way consumers use digital media portable music players and mobile phones in their vehicles.     The Ford-exclusive technology based on Microsoft Auto software, called Sync, provides consumers the convenience and flexibility to bring into their vehicle nearly any mobile phone or digital media player and operate it using voice commands or the vehicle's steering wheel or radio controls.     Ford owners will not need to worry about whether their car or truck is compatible with the latest phone or music player that hits the market. Sync seamlessly integrates the vehicle with the popular portable electronic devices of today and is upgradeable to support the devices and services of tomorrow.     "Sync is what today's generation and today's drivers demand in connectivity," says Derrick Kuzak, group vice president, product development, Ford Motor Company.  "Not only does it offer hands-free phone operation and iPod(R), Zune or MP3 player connectivity, it's built on a software platform that is upgradeable and will allow us to offer new features by simply upgrading the software."     Sync offers consumers two ways to bring electronic devices into their Ford, Lincoln and Mercury vehicles and operate them seamlessly through voice commands or steering wheel controls:          * Bluetooth, for wireless connection of phones and phones that play music.        * A USB 2.0 port for command and control and charging of digital media        players -- including the Apple iPod and Microsoft Zune -- as well as        PlaysForSure music devices and most USB media storage devices.        Supported formats include MP3, AAC, WMA, WAV and PCM.       The ability to upgrade Sync, control all portable electronic devices via voice commands, offer a USB port to connect storage devices and recharge electronics puts this technology well beyond technology available today -- including Bluetooth, hands-free offerings or portable music device connections.     "More than 80 percent of U.S. households use cell phones, and 60 million digital music devices have been sold.  That's a 50 percent increase from just 2005," Kuzak said. "With such market growth led by consumers' needs, Sync is the right new technology at the right time for Ford, Lincoln and Mercury vehicles."     Sync will debut this calendar year on the 2008 Ford Focus, Fusion, Five Hundred, Edge, Freestyle, Explorer and Sport Trac; Mercury Milan, Montego and Mountaineer; and Lincoln MKX and MKZ.  The technology will be on all Ford, Lincoln and Mercury vehicles in the near future.     "Ford and Microsoft share a vision for a future where drivers are safely connected to the people, information and entertainment they care about while they are on the road," said Bill Gates, Chairman, Microsoft Corporation. "Built on Microsoft Auto technology, Ford Sync delivers an in-car system that is an important step toward achieving this vision. Using software that bridges the automotive and consumer electronics industries, Sync will help revolutionize the driving experience by providing a simple system that intelligently connects mobile phones, music players, and more."          Sync Features:        * Voice-activated, hands-free calling: Simply press the "Push to Talk"        button on the steering wheel, and then say the name of the person you        wish to call. Sync will automatically connect with the names in the        mobile phone's contact list.        * Uninterrupted connections: No need to hang up in the middle of a cell        phone call as you enter your vehicle.  Simply touch the Telephone Button        on the steering wheel, and Sync will instantly connect to a Bluetooth        phone.        * Audible text messages: Sync will convert text messages from your phone        to audio and read it out loud.  The system is even smart enough to        translate such commonly used text messaging expressions as "LOL" and :).        You can choose to reply from any of 20 predefined responses.        * Advanced calling features: Sync includes the same features offered on        mobile phones, including caller ID, call waiting, conference calling, a        caller log, a list of contacts, a signal strength icon, and a phone        battery charge icon -- all conveniently located on the radio's display        screen.        * Voice-activated music: Browse the music collection on your digital media        player, mobile phone or USB drive by genre, album, artist and song title        using simple voice commands, such as "Play genre Rock,"        "Play < artist >," or "Play Track < song title >."        * Instant voice recognition: Sync's advanced voice recognition technology        means when you're ready to use your phone or digital music player, just        speak simple voice commands.        * Ring tone support: For supported phones, Sync will play personal ring        tones.  If you've configured unique ring tones to identify specific        callers, Sync will automatically play those, too.        * Automatic phonebook transfer: Sync will automatically and wirelessly        transfer all the names and numbers in a mobile phonebook.        * Multilingual intelligence: Sync is fluent in English, French and        Spanish.       The names of actual companies and products mentioned herein may be the trademarks of their respective owners.    SOURCE  Ford Motor Company       /CONTACT: Said Deep of Ford Motor Company, +1-313-594-0942, sdeep@ford.com      /Web site: http://www.ford.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 00:01 ET (05:01 GMT)

Headline: New Minivans Could Be Big Opportunity For Chrysler
Story: By Terry Kosdrosky   Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--The Chrysler Group's launch of its redesigned minivans this year - complete with the latest seating innovation and a new exterior look - comes as its U.S. competitors pull out of the segment, developments that could aid the struggling auto maker's turnaround.   The U.S. unit of DaimlerChrysler AG (DCX) invented the minivan in the mid-1980s and has been a market leader since. But it has faced stiff competition from Honda Motor Co.'s (HMC) Odyssey and Toyota Motor Corp.'s (TM) Sienna in recent years. All have spent time and money one-upping each other with new innovations, such as fold-flat third row seats, a split third row that folds flat and fold-flat second-row seats.   The 2008 Chrysler Town & Country and Dodge Grand Caravan will be revealed at the North American International Auto show and go on sale in the fall. They have the requisite "gee-whiz" interior innovation - second-row seats that turn 180 degrees to face the third row, with a removable table in between. That's known as "Swivel 'n Go," which builds on Chrysler's "Stow 'n Go."   Chrysler also makes an exterior statement with the 2008 model, scrapping the egg shape for a more linear, "athletic" appearance, said Chrysler design chief Trevor Creed.   With Ford Motor Co. (F) and General Motors Corp. (GM) essentially pulling out of the traditional minivan segment, Chrysler has a golden opportunity with its new model, said Erich Merkle, director of forecasting at IRN Inc. in Grand Rapids, Mich.   "This is huge for Chrysler," he said. "They've always been kind of the front-runner in the minivan segment. That fact that GM and Ford are exiting and they have a new product, that leaves all the more for Chrysler."   Merkle said it will be difficult for Honda and Toyota to fill the gap left by Ford and GM as quickly because of their capacity constraints.   He called Chrysler's minivans one of the most important vehicles of the show.   Chrysler minivan sales slumped in 2006, with the Town & Country off 12% and the Caravan off 7%. Toyota Sienna sales were up 1.5% and Honda Odyssey sales were up 2.4%.   The minivan sales decline was indicative of a general weakening in Chrysler's performance last year. The company's inventory bulged and it had to cut production and offer big incentives on its pickup trucks and SUVs.   Chrysler, which lost market share despite launching 10 new products, reported a $1.5 billion third-quarter loss. A turnaround plan is expected to be revealed next month.   Merkle said the second half of this year "should look a lot better" for Chrysler in part because of the minivans, which carry good profit margins.   He said Chrysler made the right move changing the exterior, which can carry risks.   "That's one of the things I've been looking for," Merkle said. "It speaks volumes about Chrysler's willingness to take risks. They're taking their No. 1 vehicle, their top selling vehicle, and saying they're going to shake it up. When you get your top vehicle, people tend to get very cautious. That doesn't seem to be the route Chrysler is going to be taking."   The minivans also offer other interior goodies, such as pinpoint LED lighting, retractable sun shades, one-touch power third-row folding seats and ambient halo lighting.   The Chrysler Town & Country will come in three trim levels, LX, Touring and Country Limited while the Dodge Grand Caravan will come in the SE and SXT levels.   The vans come with three powertrain options. A 3.3-liter, flex-fuel V-6 engine with a four-speed transmission or a 3.8-liter or 4.0-liter V-6 engine with a six-speed transmission.   Side-curtain airbags covering all rows are standard, as is an electronic stability program.   Creed said Chrysler "took every feature on every minivan today that we don't have that they do, and added some of our own features."   -By Terry Kosdrosky, Dow Jones Newswires; (313) 226-1251; terry.kosdrosky@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 00:44 ET (05:44 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: Chrysler CEO Confident Co Will Reach Agreement With UAW
Story: By Terry Kosdrosky      Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--Chrysler Group Chief Executive Tom LaSorda said Sunday there's "no doubt" in his mind that the auto maker can reach an agreement with the United Auto Workers union "before the end of the term" despite the tough issues facing both sides.   The master contract between the US automakers and the UAW expires later this year. Automakers have said they'd like a more competitive agreement and the union's president has indicated he'd like to hold on to benefits.   Despite expecting tough negotiations, LaSorda, speaking on the sidelines of the North American International Auto Show, said he "anticipates we'll be able to resolve things.   He also said a turnaround plan being prepared in the wake of Chrysler's $1.5 billion third-quarter loss will be "widespread" and address every area of the company. Chrysler is a unit of DaimlerChrysler AG (DCX).   LaSorda wouldnt discuss details of the turnaround strategy, saying those would come in February or early March.     -By Terry Kosdrosky, Dow Jones Newswires; (313) 226-1251; terry.kosdrosky@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 11:35 ET (16:35 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: 2 Dead, Scores Injured In India In Dispute Over Farmland
Story: CALCUTTA (AP)--Two people were killed and scores more injured in clashes between villagers and ruling Communist Party members in India's West Bengal state in a dispute over the acquisition of farmland for industrial purposes, an official said Sunday.   The violence occurred late Saturday night in Nandigram, 150 kilometers north of state capital Calcutta, local administrative official Anup Agarwal said.   West Bengal has plans to build an industrial zone in Nandigram with the help of Indonesia's Salim Group but the project has run into trouble with angry villagers refusing to give up their land.   West Bengal is ruled by the Communist Party but has keenly looked for domestic and foreign investment in the recent past.   This isn't the first time such projects have met local resistance.   Last month, there were angry protests in Singur, a village 30 kilometers northwest of Calcutta after the government sold fertile agricultural land to India's Tata Motors Ltd. (TTM), a division of Tata Group, for a factory to make small cars.     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 08:15 ET (13:15 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: Toyota Confident US Hybrid Sales Will Continue Rising
Story: By Yoshio Takahashi    Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--Toyota Motor Corp. (TM) doesn't expect that reduced tax credits for its gasoline-electric hybrid vehicles will hinder it from boosting sales of the fuel-saving vehicles this year, the head of the company's North American unit said Sunday.   The Japanese company known for making the world's first mass-produced hybrid, the Prius, aims to sell 250,000 to 300,000 hybrids in the U.S. in 2007, compared with 190,000 sold in 2006, said James E. Press, president of Toyota Motor North America. He spoke with reporters on the sidelines of the North American International Auto Show.   Tax credits for Toyota's hybrid vehicles were halved as its sales hit 60,000 vehicles in May. The reduction stemmed from a law that took effect a year ago.   Growth in sales of the Prius slowed somewhat after the reduction in tax credits, the Toyota executive said. "But that hasn't stopped" the trend of year-over-year growth, he said.   Customers' appetite for the Prius remains solid, even as they now try to spend less to buy the model. They tend to buy the model without navigation systems, though the version equipped with such systems used to be popular, he said.     -By Yoshio Takahashi, Dow Jones Newswires; 813-5255-2929; yoshio.takahashi@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 14:36 ET (19:36 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: Bristol Airport Closes Runway As Of 1430 GMT Sunday -2-
Story: A spokesman for Bristol airport said that the runway had been closed in order to "fast-track" the resurfacing. Budget airline Easyjet (EZJ.LN) became the fourth carrier to transfer flights away from Bristol on Saturday, when it opted to operate instead out of nearby Cardiff airport.   Three other airlines, Aer Lingus (EIL1.DB), XL and Air Malta, temporarily relocated to Cardiff as well.   Bristol airport said that detailed assessments were carried out Sunday morning on the impact of additional grooving on test strips of the temporary runway surface.   "These have proved satisfactory in terms of further increasing the drainage of surface water on the temporary sections of the runway which is in the process of being resurfaced," the statement said.   The Civil Aviation Authority has no objection to extra grooving work that has been proposed. Bristol airport said the additional grooving and the CAA's stance gave it confidence that the airlines would resume operations at Bristol.   "We will continue to liaise fully with our airlines partners and provide them with all the information they need to operate from the airport," Bristol International Airport Managing Director Andrew Skipp said in the statement.   Company Web site: http://www.bristolairport.co.uk   -By Victoria Howley, Dow Jones Newswires; 44 20 7842 9261; victoria.howley@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 10:17 ET (15:17 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: GM CFO Says Co Won't Provide Earnings Guidance In 2007
Story: By John D. Stoll      Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--General Motors Corp.'s (GM) chief financial officer on Sunday said the auto maker doesn't plan to return to furnishing formal earnings guidance in 2007, but the auto maker will lay out some benchmarks for the year during an analyst conference on Thursday.   Fritz Henderson, talking on the sidelines of a GM presentation at the North American International Auto Show, said relevant company executives, including himself, will continue to be barred from trading GM shares due to the moratorium on guidance. GM quit supplying formal guidance in 2005 as uncertainty about the operating environment added extra challenges to forecasting.   In 2006, Henderson had indicated the company might return to giving guidance once certain issues were ironed out, including the company's move to sell a controlling stake in the General Motors Acceptance Corp. lending arm and resolving an ongoing conflict at Delphi Corp. (DPHIQ). Delphi filed for bankruptcy in 2005 and GM, which is Delphi's former parent and largest customer, has spent a good deal of the past 16 months ironing out its financial obligation to the parts supplier.   GM Chief Executive Rick Wagoner on Thursday said the major issues that need to be sorted out at Delphi have been largely clarified. While some hurdles remain, such as forging a concrete Delphi labor agreement with the United Auto Workers union, GM estimates its financial obligation to Delphi at between $6 billion and $7.5 billion, much of which has been accounted for in non-cash charges.   Wagoner, speaking during a roundtable with reporters, said that the company has a plan to lay out its "plus and minus" benchmarks at the analyst meeting Thursday. GM last utilized a similar venue to lay out cost-cut targets and other benchmarks.   Wagoner said the company expects to continue to improve earnings on an ongoing basis and not to experience a "plateau." GM improved earnings by $3.5 billion in the first nine months of 2006 against the backdrop of a challenging U.S. market, Wagoner said. He said GM's continued losses aren't remarkable but said the improvement is significant.     -By John D. Stoll, Dow Jones Newswires; (313) 226-1249; john.stoll@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 15:58 ET (20:58 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: : 2008 Ford Focus Demonstrated Ford's Commitment to Small Cars
Story: DETROIT, Jan. 7 /PRNewswire-FirstCall/ -- The 2008 Ford Focus is redesigned inside and out with a bold new exterior, a modern interior and a long list of new safety and technology features, including Ford Sync(TM) -- Ford's exclusive fully integrated, voice-activated in-car communications and entertainment system for mobile phones and digital media players.     Also new is a sporty two-door Focus coupe, which is designed to attract new and younger buyers in the growing small car market. Small cars make up the largest vehicle segment in the U.S. today, and growth is expected to continue. "We're expanding our commitment to small cars, as that is where many of our customers are headed. The new Focus is substantially upgraded, and it's the start of several new small cars coming from Ford in the next several years," said Mark Fields, Ford's president of The Americas.     "We've packed more style, more comfort and more features into the new Focus, but we've left the fuel economy as strong as ever." On sale in the fall of 2007, the new Focus will offer fuel economy rivaling smaller vehicles. With its fuel efficient 2.0-liter engine and approximately 60 pounds less weight, the new 2008 Focus is expected to deliver real-world fuel economy similar to today's model, despite added content and a stiffer body. Currently, Focus is among the segment's best with a U.S. EPA rating of 37 miles per gallon on the highway.        Bold details bring new Focus exterior to life     In shaping the new Focus, the design team looked to the Ford Fusion, drawing on its prominent chrome-bar grille design, flared wheel arches and crisp lines to create a small car that's stylish and sporty. Several bold details bring the exterior of the new Focus to life. One is the taut character line that runs from the taillights across the doors just below the door handles and then snaps down at the front wheel well. Another example is the four separate creases incorporated into the hood.     The headlights are a design story by themselves. Horizontal bars with a matte surface run through the reflection area, visually connecting the headlights with a sweeping line running through the chrome-bar grille.        New interior built to be a second home on wheels     "We've taken cues from fashion and home design and translated them into a fresh new Focus interior," says Lon Zaback, Focus chief designer. "We've created a second home on wheels with such details as ambient lighting that is popular in homes today. We've also used higher-quality materials -- like the silver metallic finishes you see in appliances -- to make the overall package more inviting." Customers can order a new ambient lighting package that places tiny LEDs inside the front and rear cupholders and in the footwells. The LEDs can highlight the cabin in any of seven different colors through a dash-mounted switch."     Overall, the interior is modern and quieter. The 2008 Focus features a new acoustic windshield, thicker side glass in the front doors and additional sound deadening materials throughout the cabin. A "top-of-dash" display -- positioned at eye-level on the center stack -- features a message center that is easier to read when driving. In addition, a new center console design replaces the traditional "brick" pattern for the radio and heating/air conditioning controls. It also houses a standard auxiliary audio input jack and two power points.        Ford Sync helps Focus owners stay connected     To meet customer demand for must-have technologies, Ford Sync is available in the new Focus. Developed in association with Microsoft, Sync is Ford's new factory installed, voice-activated in-car communications and entertainment system for mobile phones and digital music players.     Sync connects to cellular phones and downloads personal features, such as phone books and ring tones. Using Sync's voice recognition software, drivers can place and receive calls and receive text messages using the vehicle's audio system. Users can even maintain a cell phone conversation while entering or exiting the vehicle.     Sync also offers hands-free, voice-activated control for nearly any digital media player, including the Apple iPod(R), Microsoft Zune(TM), "Plays for Sure" players and most USB storage devices. Even MP3 files saved on flash memory sticks can be played by simply inserting the stick into system's USB port.     Because Sync is fully upgradeable, Focus owners will never need to worry about whether their car is compatible with the latest phone or music player that hits the market.        Reworked suspension and stiffer body give Focus a better ride     For 2008, the Focus's curb weight is reduced by 60 pounds, even though the body structure is stiffer. In retuning the body structure, engineers concentrated on such specific areas as the roof structure, package tray, rear floor area and door systems. They also added a stiffened cross-car beam under the instrument panel for even better lateral stiffness. The result is sharper steering and handling with improved ride quality at the same time.     The 2008 Focus features a 2.0-liter, 16-valve, four-cylinder engine with a new air intake system and new cooling system delivering an estimated 136 hp. Available in states adopting the California emission standards is a super-clean Duratec 20E engine that qualifies as a Partial Zero Emissions Vehicle (PZEV).        Ford's Personal Safety System(R) is standard on all 2008 Focus model     The 2008 Focus, in addition to Ford's Personal Safety System, comes standard with side air bags and side air curtains.  The advanced side air curtains -- Ford's Safety Canopy(TM) -- feature "roll-fold" technology. If occupants are resting their heads against a window, the curtain is designed to slide between the glass and occupants as it inflates. In the event of a rollover, the curtains remain inflated for several seconds to enhance protection during an extended crash event.     Ford's Personal Safety System is a comprehensive collection of passive safety features for the front passengers. The system includes dual-deployment front air bags, energy absorbing safety belts, load limiting retractors and pretensioners, all which will help to create one of the safest cabins in its segment.        About Ford Motor Company     Ford Motor Company, a global automotive industry leader based in Dearborn, Mich., manufactures and distributes automobiles in 200 markets across six continents. With about 300,000 employees and more than 100 plants worldwide, the company's core and affiliated automotive brands include Aston Martin, Ford, Jaguar, Land Rover, Lincoln, Mazda, Mercury and Volvo. Its automotive-related services include Ford Motor Credit Company. For more information regarding Ford's products, please visit http://www.fordvehicles.com.        Additional media information is available at http://www.media.ford.com.    SOURCE  Ford Motor Company       /CONTACT: Tammera Hallums, +1-313-594-2120, thallums@ford.com, Alan Hall, +1-313-594-3744, ahall32@ford.com, Mark Schirmer, +1-313-390-8647, mschirme@ford.com, all of Ford Motor Company      /Web site: http://www.ford.com      /Web site: http://www.fordvehicles.com      /Web site: http://www.media.ford.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 00:01 ET (05:01 GMT)

Headline: 2nd UPDATE: Chrysler CEO Confident Of Pact With UAW
Story: (Updates throughout with additional comments from LaSorda on a UAW health care deal and comments from chief operating officer.)        By Terry Kosdrosky      Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--Chrysler Group Chief Executive Tom LaSorda said Sunday there's "no doubt" in his mind that the auto maker can reach an agreement with the United Auto Workers union "before the end of the term" despite the tough issues facing both sides.   The master contract between the US automakers and the UAW expires later this year. Automakers have said they'd like a more competitive agreement and the union's president has indicated he'd like to hold on to benefits. Chrysler is a unit of DaimlerChrysler AG (DCX).   Despite expecting tough negotiations, LaSorda, speaking on the sidelines of the North American International Auto Show, said he "anticipates we'll be able to resolve things."   U.S. auto makers are expected to try to address rising health care costs and the controversial "Jobs Bank" program that pays workers nearly full pay and benefits while on layoff.   Chrysler Group Chief Operating Officer Eric Ridenour, during a separate interview with Dow Jones Newswires, said of the Jobs Bank: "Certainly that would be probably one of the things that would come up" during negotiations. He woudln't specify any of Chrysler's talking points with the UAW.   LaSorda's optimism comes even though the UAW has not given Chrysler the health care concessions it gave General Motors Corp. (GM) and Ford Motor Co. (F). LaSorda, speaking during a roundtable interview with reporters, said Chrysler still hopes to get a similar health care deal before talks start on the master agreement later this summer.   The UAW has argued that Chryslers is in a different financial position than GM and Ford.   But LaSorda said Sunday that Chrysler gave the union more financial information at the end of 2006 and he hopes a dialogue with the UAW begins soon after this week.   He said Chrysler is at a "competitive disadvantage" with Ford and GM without a similar deal.   Despite that difference with the union, LaSorda said he remains confident the auto maker will be able to reach a new master agreement before the deadline expires.   He said Chrysler and the UAW have a good history of identifying the problems facing them and solving them at the bargaining table.        Turnaround Plan To Be Widespread     LaSorda also said a turnaround plan being prepared in the wake of Chrysler's $1.5 billion third-quarter loss will be "widespread" and address every area of the company.   LaSorda wouldnt discuss details of the turnaround strategy, saying those would come in February or early March. When asked if the plan would include plant closings, he said it hasn't been decided.   He also said he's taking a look at the advertising and marketing for each of the auto maker's brands - Chrysler, Dodge and Jeep - to make sure they're getting the right advertising and market message. LaSorda took over responsibility for U.S. sales after the departure of former sales chief Joe Eberhardt in late 2006.   LaSorda said he's spent a lot of time looking at each brand's message.   "The question is, am I fully aligned with the brand, brand equity, brand values with my advertising... and I think we can improve upon that," he said.   LaSorda said Chrysler expects to hear a decision from the DaimlerChrysler supervisory board and Chinese authorities within 30 to 60 days on its joint venture proposal with Chinese auto maker Chery Automobile Co. to build a subcompact car for North America and other markets.   Chrysler has said it wants to offer a subcompact car in North America as consumers shift away from larger vehicles, but also said it's difficult to build a cost-competitive model in North America.   LaSorda said he expects to make another trip to the White House this year and plans to meet the new Congressional leadership before the end of the second quarter. "The earlier the better," he said.   LaSorda and his counterparts at GM and Ford met with President George W. Bush late last year to discuss trade, energy and currency policies, among other issues impacting the automotive sector. The Big 3 executives have complained over the past year that certain policies give their foreign competitors an unfair advantage.        Hopes to Gain U.S. Share     Chrysler hit a bump in the road last year when inventory levels spiked amid a downturn in sales of pickup trucks and SUVs. After gaining market share in 2005, Chrysler's U.S. sales were down 7% to 2.14 million vehicles in 2006.   LaSorda said Chrysler will focus on "profitable growth" in 2007 but didn't give any projections, noting that 2006 was a down year   Ridenour said he would like to see an increase in U.S. market share for Chrysler in 2007, given the new products launched late last year and with eight new products launching in 2007. Overall, he said 2007 U.S. auto sales likely will be flat to slightly down compared with 2007.    "Within that, how do you do from the standpoint of share?," he said. "And certainly with the new products hitting and getting in full stride, we'd like to see an increase in that. And as you take those two together, hopefully that means a net increase in total units."   He wouldln't give a specific projections.   LaSorda said a priority this year is to help out Chrysler's dealers, who also were stung by the inventory buildup.   "We let them down here somewhat in 2006," LaSorda said. "We're going to make sure that our focus is on profit from great products, keep the inventory levels balanced so they can make money again."     -By Terry Kosdrosky, Dow Jones Newswires; (313) 226-1251; terry.kosdrosky@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 15:13 ET (20:13 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: UPDATE: Bristol Airport Closes Runway Until Mon Morning
Story: (This updates an item that ran at 1517 GMT with comment from easyJet.)   LONDON (Dow Jones)--Bristol International airport said Sunday that it was had closed its runway as of 1430 GMT and that flights after that would either be diverted or canceled.   The arrangement will remain in place until Monday morning, the statement said.   Some airlines operating at Bristol have expressed concerns about the surface of the temporary sections of the runway during an ongoing resurfacing program in wet conditions.   A spokesman for Bristol airport said that the runway had been closed in order to "fast-track" the resurfacing. Budget airline easyJet (EZJ.LN) became the fourth carrier to transfer flights away from Bristol on Saturday, when it opted to operate instead out of nearby Cardiff airport.   EasyJet said Sunday that it "will operate 60% of its Bristol operation in and out of Cardiff. However, 20 flights will have to be canceled. EasyJet expects to resume normal operations from Bristol International Airport within the next few days once the maintenance is complete."   It added that passengers must still check in at Bristol airport and that easyJet will transfer them to Cardiff. It said that easyJet had no facilities in Cardiff to check in passengers.   Three other airlines, Aer Lingus (EIL1.DB), XL and Air Malta, temporarily relocated to Cardiff as well.   Bristol airport said that detailed assessments were carried out Sunday morning on the impact of additional grooving on test strips of the temporary runway surface.   "These have proved satisfactory in terms of further increasing the drainage of surface water on the temporary sections of the runway which is in the process of being resurfaced," the statement said.   The Civil Aviation Authority has no objection to extra grooving work that has been proposed. Bristol airport said the additional grooving and the CAA's stance gave it confidence that the airlines would resume operations at Bristol.   "We will continue to liaise fully with our airlines partners and provide them with all the information they need to operate from the airport," Bristol International Airport Managing Director Andrew Skipp said in the statement.   Company Web site: http://www.bristolairport.co.uk   -By Victoria Howley, Dow Jones Newswires; 44 20 7842 9261; victoria.howley@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 10:57 ET (15:57 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: Volkswagen Grp 2006 Sales +9.3% At 5.73M Vehicles -2-
Story: The core VW brand saw sales rise 10% on the year in 2006 to a new record of 3.39 million passenger cars, fueled by rising demand in China, South America and Western Europe.   VW's troubled Spanish Seat brand eked out a 1.9% increase last year compared with 2005 to 430,000 deliveries to customers.   The Czech Skoda brand posted a new sales record in 2006 with 550,000 passenger cars, up 11.7% on the year, fueled by strong gains in Central and Eastern Europe as well as the parent company's German home market.   The British Bentley luxury brand increased sales by 7.1% on the year in 2006 to 9,200 vehicles, which also marks a new record for the division, the company said.   Sales for the Italian Lamborghini brand jumped 30% in 2006 to 2,087 of its high-performance cars.   Volkswagen said it sold 47 Bugatti cars in the year of the brand's relaunch.     Company Web site: http://www.volkswagen.com     -By Christoph Rauwald, Dow Jones Newswires; +49 69 29 725 512; christoph.rauwald@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 09:49 ET (14:49 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK: GM Says Volt Isn't Weird Science
Story: Edited by Paul Vigna     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES       (call: 201-938-5172; email: paul.vigna@dowjones.com)       AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK can be found using N/DJMT and I/AUT     3:25 (Dow Jones) GM CEO Rick Wagoner says the Chevy Volt electric car "isn't about science projects." The auto maker has set aside hundreds of millions of dollars to get the electric car started, but Wagoner indicates the company will spend significantly more than $500M to make it a reality. Wagoner says the company needs to build more than the 1,000 or so electric cars the company did in its last electric car effort, the abandoned EV1 program, and adds their vision is clearer this time. Instead, GM would ideally like to build "hundreds of thousands, (even) millions a year...this is an opportunity to deliver results." He concedes, however, there are question marks around the technology. "Production time will depend on development of battery technology," he says. (JDS/PI)   2:16 (Dow Jones) GM Vice Chairman Bob Lutz called it an "inconvenient truth" that his company has indeed started development of a new "E-Flex" vehicle, the Chevrolet Volt, which run on electricity as well as biodiesel, ethanol and, yes, gasoline. The Volt has a sporty look, WSJ.com observes, and Lutz noted an electric vehicle can also "look good." The Volt can drive 40 miles before other fuels need to help recharge and Lutz emphasized that 78% of Americans live within 20 miles of work. He said if someone drove to work, ran nearby errands and charged the car every night, the owner would never have to buy gasoline for the lifetime of the vehicle, he said. For now, though, the Volt remains only an intriguing concept. (MS)   (http://blogs.wsj.com/autoshow/)   1:26 (Dow Jones) In the minutes leading up to Chrysler Group's big auto show press conference, there were giant loafs of bread flanking the stage. A kitchen counter was in the middle, as if on a cooking show. Irreverent slices of cartoon bread danced on a giant screen.   What was the theme for this revamped minivan unveiling event - the "best thing since sliced bread" or "something's cooking at Chrysler"? Nope. Instead, it was Chrysler Group's focus on its "bread and butter" vehicles. The DaimlerChrysler AG (DCX) unit rolled out the latest versions of its Dodge Caravan and Chrysler Town & Country minivans, replete with a host of gadgets and options. Not listed: the wood paneling seen on the old Plymouth Voyager minivan, also rolled out as Chrysler touted it's long pioneering position in the vehicle segment.   Chrysler President Tom LaSorda was joined on stage by celebrity chef Bobby Flay, and the two made a couple of quick dishes that represent the Chrysler and Dodge brands - spicy pork loin with mango for Dodge and a smooth chocolate ganache cake for Chrysler.   When LaSorda took a turn icing the cake, Flay told the executive, "I can tell you've spent a lot of time in the hot kitchen," to which LaSorda replied, "The kitchen's been pretty hot lately, I'll tell you," a reference to Chrysler's tough 2006. (JDK, TKS)   1:08 (Dow Jones) Ford's (F) new leader, Alan Mulally, looked like a lifer in his appearance at the company's press conference. Driven out in a glistening new 500 sedan, Mulally was poised and energetic in discussing Ford's cars and prospects, sounding much like a man who's excited about what he's doing. After the event, North American head Mark Fields - who matched Mulally in the enthusiasm department - said he expects the auto maker's sales will be down slightly, with light vehicle sales of roughly 16.4M, as the US economy slows down. Fields expects GDP of 2%-2.5%, with a moderating job market and weak housing market. (PJV)   12:40 (Dow Jones) Was that a press conference or a rock concert? Ford's (F) flashy press conference featured deafening rock music, a light show and five giant video screens. Executives like Bill Ford Jr. and Mark Fields were driven onto the stage in glistening cars and greeted like guitar heroes. The music was so loud it drowned out the engine on Ford's concept muscle car, the Interceptor. Even Bill Gates was trotted out via satellite to talk about Ford and Microsoft's (MSFT) "Sync" project. 2006 was difficult, Bill Ford said, and 2007 will be pivotal, but the company's laid the foundation for a better Ford. (PJV)   11:05 (Dow Jones) Johnson Control (JCI) is trying to beef up the gadget-connection capability in cars, an issue in the spotlight at this year's North American International Auto Show with the Ford/Microsoft deal. JCI on Sunday unveiled its Mobile Device Gateway, which would allow drivers to use Bluetooth, USB and serial ports to plug in cell phones, MP3 players and other devices and use them as if they were factory-installed. JCI is working with automakers on making it available in 2010 and "maybe even a little earlier," says Scott Wright, vice president of electronic sales and marketing. The system expands on JCI's current Bluetooth system. (TAK)   10:53 (Dow Jones) The media are descending on Detroit. The centennial North American auto show kicks off today, with a full slate of events and hoards of journalists jockeying for position. GM is building the early buzz, with its glitzy runway show last night and its fairly surprising sweep of the North American car and truck awards this morning. The company also has a noon press conference where it will unveil its latest concept car, the Chevy Volt, and talk about getting back into the electric car market - just as soon as it develops a new type of battery. (PJV)     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 15:25 ET (20:25 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: GERMAN PRESS: VW Brand CEO Bernhard To Leave Co Jan 31
Story: FRANKFURT (Dow Jones)--The chief executive of Volkswagen AG's (VOW.XE) core brand Volkswagen will leave the company January 31, weekly German magazine Der Spiegel said Sunday ahead of publication Monday.   Wolfgang Bernhard has decided to leave the company because of the restructuring plans of the company's new CEO Martin Winterkorn which would leave Bernhard with the responsibility for production, but not for development and sales and distribution, according to Der Spiegel.   German weekly Focus will also report Monday that Bernhard said the restructuring will severely harm the image of the Volkswagen brand.   Volkswagen spokesman Hartwig von Sass declined to comment on the reports.     Magazine Web site: http://www.spiegel.de                      http://www.focus.de     -Frankfurt Bureau, Dow Jones Newswires; 49-69-29725-500.     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 08:18 ET (13:18 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: : Mobile Beachside Cafe Rolls In Weight-Loss Season 2007 With South Beach Diet(R) From Kraft
Story: Celebrity trainer Ramona Braganza shares food, fitness and fun       NORTHFIELD, Ill., Jan. 7 /PRNewswire/ -- Let the countdown to your winter shape up begin! As the New Year approaches, many Americans resolve to get in shape and lose weight. To help dieters maintain their New Year's diet resolutions, Kraft is bringing the beach to those in need of a winter warm-up! The South Beach Diet(R) "Beach in a Box Cafe" from Kraft will brave snow, sleet and rain to brighten diet season and deliver delicious and nutritious foods and fitness tips fitting the principles of the best-selling diet.        (Photo:  http://www.newscom.com/cgi-bin/prnh/20070107/CGSU001A )     Two 35-foot long warm, sunny beachside cafes will travel across the country throughout January.  Floor-to-ceiling Plexiglas windows encase the inviting white-sand beach, complete with palm trees, shade umbrellas and a beachside snack bar, serving nutritious and delicious South Beach Diet(R) foods. The South Beach Diet(R) "Beach in a Box Cafe" from Kraft will visit popular venues in nine major cities.        Train on the Beach Celebrity-Style     To help make New Year's resolutions fun and achievable, celebrity fitness trainer Ramona Braganza will make appearances at selected "Beach in a Box Cafe" stops.  She'll demonstrate functional fitness, which includes core and cardio exercises, based on the principles of The South Beach Diet fitness program. The exercises don't require special equipment and can be done at home, outside ... even in the office!     "Celebrities work hard to get in shape, but they face fitness challenges like the rest of us," Braganza said. "They have hectic schedules and can't always find time to exercise or eat right.  What I recommend to everyone is this: find an effective exercise routine that fits into your lifestyle and keep convenient and nutritious foods on hand," she added.     At select "Beach in a Box Cafe" tour stops in New York, Boston, Washington, D.C. and Boston, passer-bys can meet Ramona Braganza -- who's trained Hollywood celebrities including Jessica Alba, Halle Berry and Jessica Biel. Top local trainers will make appearances at other tour stops.        Life is Better on the Beach(TM)     Heat lamps will simulate the warmth of the beach while retractable awnings protect "Beach in a Box Cafe" visitors from the January outdoor elements. Guests can enjoy the blissful beach atmosphere under a shade umbrella and sample delicious, convenient South Beach Diet(R) foods from Kraft, including Microwaveable Pizza and Sandwich Wraps.  All visitors will receive South Beach Diet(R) product coupons, Cereal Bars -- perfect for on-the-go snacking -- and a diet solutions mini-magazine featuring the latest South Beach Diet(R) news, delicious recipes and tips for choosing convenient, great-tasting products.             Calling All Beach-Lovers       The South Beach Diet(R) "Beach in a Box" tour is as follows         New York City         January 3-10       Boston                January 12-15       Philadelphia          January 17-20       Baltimore             January 23-26       Washington, DC        January 28-30       Indianapolis          January 4-6       Pittsburgh            January 9-13       Chicago               January 16-20       Minneapolis           January 24-28         Visit http://www.southbeachdiet.com/kraft for more "Beach in a Box Cafe" details and for a downloadable brochure of sample exercises. The entire fitness program is on http://www.southbeachdiet.com .        The South Beach Diet and South Beach Diet foods from Kraft     The South Beach Diet is a weight-loss plan that promotes the right carbs and encourages people to eat a variety of foods, such as lean sources of protein, whole grains, fruits and vegetables, reduced fat cheeses and dairy products and right fats like olive and canola oil.     The South Beach Diet(R) foods from Kraft, now offering more than 50 items, bring variety and convenience to dieters, or people who just want to eat right, succeed this New Year and throughout the year.  And many of the foods help satisfy hunger with protein or fiber.        Kraft Food's Commitment to Health & Wellness     Kraft has been a leader in marketing products that help people eat and live better, offering a range of nutritious alternatives like fat-free and sugar-free products, as well as those that leverage emerging health and wellness trends.  Kraft's product portfolio provides a broad range of options for consumers to choose different products for various eating occasions.        About Kraft Foods     Kraft Foods (NYSE: KFT) is the world's second-largest food and beverage company. For more than 100 years, we've been dedicated to helping people around the world eat and live better. Hundreds of millions of times a day, in more than 150 countries, consumers reach for their favorite Kraft brands including Kraft cheeses and dinners, Jacobs, Gevalia and Maxwell House coffees, Oscar Mayer meats, DiGiorno pizzas, Oreo cookies, Ritz and Wheat Thins crackers and chips, Philadelphia cream cheese, Milka and Cote d'Or chocolates, Honey Bunches of Oats cereals, Good Seasons salad dressings and Tang refreshment beverage. They've also started adding our Tassimo hot beverage system, South Beach Diet(R) line and a growing range of better-for-you Sensible Solution products to their shopping baskets, continually expanding their list of Kraft favorites. For more information, visit kraft.com.        About The South Beach Diet(R)     Preventive cardiologist Arthur Agatston, MD developed The South Beach Diet(R) to help his patients whose weight and blood chemistries were not improving. His balanced approach to nutrition and weight management proved highly effective and later served as the basis for his first non-academic work, The South Beach Diet(R). Subsequent books published under The South Beach Diet(R) title also became bestsellers, including: The South Beach Diet Cookbook (2004); The South Beach Diet Good Fats Good Carbs Guide (2004), The South Beach Quick & Easy Cookbook (2005), and The South Beach Diet Dining Guide (2005), The South Beach Diet Parties & Holidays Cookbook (2006). The South Beach Diet(R) - "Changing the Way America Eats" http://www.southbeachdiet.com    SOURCE  Kraft Foods       /CONTACT: Lyndsie Jackson, +1-312-988-2055, ljackson@webershandwick.com , or Sydney Lindner, +1-608-285-6820, sydney.lindner@kraft.com , both for Kraft Foods      /Web site: http://www.southbeachdiet.com      /Web site: http://www.southbeachdiet.com/kraft      /Web site: http://kraft.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 09:00 ET (14:00 GMT)

Headline: Bidders Tightlipped On Bombay Bourse Bidding Position
Story: By Victoria Howley     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     LONDON (Dow Jones)--Deutsche Boerse AG (DB1.XE) declined to comment Sunday on Indian press reports that said it was one of five parties shortlisted to acquire a 26% stake in the Bombay Stock Exchange.   India's Business Standard newspaper quoted an industry source Friday as saying that Deutsche Boerse had been shortlisted for the stake along with London Stock Exchange (LSE.LN), Nasdaq Stock Market Inc. (NDAQ), NYSE Group Inc. (NYX) and the Singapore Stock Exchange.   The Bombay Stock Exchange, LSE, Nasdaq, NYSE and the Singapore Stock Exchange weren't available for comment.   The Bombay Stock Exchange will offer the stake to a maximum of three strategic investors, and will give preference to overseas bourses that have better technological skills in derivatives, the paper said.   Last month, the Reserve Bank of India said that foreign investment of up to 49% would be allowed in stock exchanges, depositories and clearing corporations.   Company Web site: http://www.deutsche-boerse.com   -By Victoria Howley, Dow Jones Newswires; 44 20 7842 9261; victoria.howley@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 08:26 ET (13:26 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: Flights Canceled, Trains Delayed In Japan Due To Storms
Story: TOKYO (AP)--Strong winds and heavy snow engulfed much of Japan on Sunday, prompting the cancellation of more than 100 flights to and from an international airport in central Japan and delaying the high-speed bullet train service, officials said.   The Meteorological Agency warned of strong winds in northern to western Japan and heavy snow in the main northern island of Hokkaido and areas along the Sea of Japan that stretches from northeastern to southwestern Japan.   At Chubu Centrair International Airport, 109 domestic flights and 29 international flights to and from the airport have been canceled since Sunday morning, according to airport spokesman Yuki Hasegawa. Six more international flights bound for the airport have been diverted to two other airports in Japan, he said.   Central Japan Railway Co. (9022.TO), or JR Tokai, which operates bullet trains linking Tokyo to western Japan, said on its Web site that some trains have been delayed due to snow.   Up to 80 centimeters of snow was forecast for Hokkaido and parts of northwestern Japan by Monday morning, the agency said in a statement.     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 01:40 ET (06:40 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: : Hesperian Capital Management Ltd. Announces Significant Investment In Black Diamond Income Fund>
Story: CALGARY, Jan. 5 /CNW/ - Hesperian Capital Management Ltd., which manages a strategically focused group of public and private investment funds, announced today that it has acquired control of an additional 281,500 shares of Black Diamond Income Fund (the "Corporation").    The shares were purchased by the Norrep Fund, Norrep Pooled Fund and Norrep II Class of Norrep Opportunities Corp. As a result of this investment, Hesperian controls 1,028,600 common shares, which represent approximately a 19.24% undiluted interest and a 12.86% fully diluted interest in the Corporation.    The Black Diamond Income Fund shares are held by Hesperian for investment purposes, and will be reviewed by Hesperian's management on a regular basis. Management may increase or decrease its share ownership of this investment in the future. A copy of the report filed by Hesperian in connection with the acquisition, as required under applicable securities legislation, may be obtained by contacting the office of Hesperian at 1-877-531-9355.    Hesperian Capital Management Ltd. is a Calgary-based investment manager that manages the Norrep Group of Funds. They have over $700 million in combined assets.    Visit www.hesperiancapital.com for more details about Hesperian and the Norrep Group of Funds.    Certain information set forth in this press release, including a discussion of future plans and operations, contains forward-looking statements that involve substantial known and unknown risks and uncertainties. These forward-looking statements are subject to numerous risks and uncertainties, some of which are beyond management's control, including but not limited to, the impact of general economic conditions, industry conditions, fluctuation of commodity prices, fluctuation of foreign exchange rates, environmental risks industry competition, availability of qualified personnel and management, stock market volatility, timely and cost effective access to sufficient capital from internal and external sources. Actual results, performance or achievement could differ from those expressed in or implied by these forward-looking statements.    %SEDAR: 00017183E         /CONTACT: Keith Leslie, CFA, Vice-President, Hesperian Capital Management Ltd., (403) 531-2650, keith@hesperiancapital.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 10:38 ET (15:38 GMT)

Headline: : New TwinForce Engine Concept Delivers V-8 Power and Performance V-6 Fuel Economy
Story: DETROIT, Jan 7. /PRNewswire-FirstCall/ -- The Lincoln MKR concept, unveiled today at the 2007 North American International Auto Show, introduces a new engine technology that delivers V-8 power and performance with V-6 fuel economy.  The new technology, named TwinForce(TM), will appear on future Lincoln and Ford vehicles.     TwinForce uses direct injection technology and turbocharging. These technologies are common in diesel engines, but have only recently been combined for use in gasoline engines.     "Everything we do is driven by our customers," said Derrick Kuzak, group vice president, Global Product Development. "Our TwinForce engine technology is a key element of how we're going after fuel economy gains without asking anyone to give up performance."     TwinForce's direct-injection fuel system is different than conventional port fuel-injected gasoline engines. Instead of squirting gasoline into the engine cylinder head, it directly injects gasoline into the engine's cylinders at high pressures.     Direct-injection fuel systems can more precisely control when and how much fuel is injected into the engine cylinders, allowing for more efficient burn and improved combustion control that delivers optimal performance and fuel economy.     Ford's new Duratec 35 all-aluminum V-6, named a 10 Best Engine by Ward's, is the foundation for the TwinForce technology found in the Lincoln MKR concept.     The Lincoln MKR's engine is flex-fuel capable, providing the driver with the flexibility to switch back and forth between gasoline and E-85 ethanol. At Ford, flexible fuel is an important step toward development of more efficient, renewable biofuels that can provide energy security as well as environmental benefits.     Combining the high octane found in E-85 or premium gasoline with TwinForce technology allows the Lincoln MKR's V-6 to deliver 415 horsepower and 400 pound-feet of torque -- an impressive 118 horsepower per liter.     To achieve this type of performance from a V-8 would require an engine displacement of 6.0-liters or larger. As a result of the smaller V-6, the Lincoln MKR concept delivers 15 percent better fuel economy than a V-8 with similar performance.     In North America, the market is growing for the new TwinForce technology. Ford Motor Company already has several direct-injection equipped 4-cylinder engines in production, including a 1.8-liter launched in the 2003 Ford Mondeo and the 2.3-liter turbocharged engine developed by Mazda for the 2006 MazdaSpeed6.     The TwinForce technology used in the Lincoln MKR represents Ford's first application of direct injection on a V-6 engine. Its development was led by Ford Powertrain Research and Advanced Engineering, the same group leading the production design and development of this technology in a pilot program intended to speed the time to market with the new engine.        About Ford Motor Company     Ford Motor Company, a global automotive industry leader based in Dearborn, Mich., manufactures and distributes automobiles in 200 markets across six continents. With about 300,000 employees and more than 100 plants worldwide, the company's core and affiliated automotive brands include Aston Martin, Ford, Jaguar, Land Rover, Lincoln, Mazda, Mercury and Volvo. Its automotive- related services include Ford Motor Credit Company. For more information regarding Ford's products, please visit http://www.fordvehicles.com.    SOURCE  Ford Motor Company       /CONTACT: Nick Twork, +1-313-598-0481, ntwork1@ford.com, or Said Deep, +1-313-594-0942, sdeep@ford.com      /Web site: http://www.ford.com      /Web site: http://www.fordvehicles.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 00:02 ET (05:02 GMT)

Headline: Daimler's Smart Expects Fortwo Sales To Rise 07-Pres
Story: - -   *Daimler's Smart Expects Fortwo Sales To Rise 07-Pres *Daimler's Smart Unit On Track For Break-Even 07- Pres *Turnaround Of Daimler's Smart Unit Is Sustainable -Pres =INTERVIEW:Daimler's Smart Expects Sales To Rise 07-Pres  *************************************  ***EMBARGO **** GMT/15:00ET, DAY 07/01***Detroit (unedited)  *************************************     By Christoph Rauwald   Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--The president and chief executive of DaimlerChrysler AG's (DCX) Smart minicar division Ulrich Walker said Sunday sales for the Fortwo model are expected to rise in 2007.   "We're expecting the new model to push sales this year above last year's level," Walker told Dow Jones Newswires at the North American International Auto Show.   Walker said the division is "on the safe side" to reach break-even this year.   Following a wide-ranging restructuring program at Smart amid painful losses, DaimlerChrysler aims to reach break-even at Smart by focusing on the two-seater Fortwo model, nearly a decade after the brand's launch in October 1998. The tiny two-seater Fortwo is the brand's only model after the company ceased production of a four-seater and a roadster model.   The Smart division saw deliveries fall 22% on the year to 112,100 vehicles in full-year 2006. The Fortwo accounted for around 70% of the unit's sales last year as sales of the Roadtser and Fortwo model phased out. Walker said the internal targets have been "more than fulfilled" ahead of the upcoming model changeover, without elaborating further.   Smart is set to launch a new version of its tiny two-seater model in April 2007, and plans a U.S. debut for the brand in the first quarter 2008. For the entry in the U.S. market, DaimlerChrysler signed a General Distributor Agreement, or GDA, with UnitedAuto Group Inc. (UAG) last year. According to previous company statement, DaimlerChrysler estimates the "market potential" to be around 20,000 sales per year.   "I think there a lot of people out there who are looking for low costs of ownership and are concerned about traffic congestion," UnitedAuto Group's CEO Roger Penske told Dow Jones Newswires in Detroit. He declined to give a specific sales target for the Smart brand in the U.S.   "Smart sold around 4,000 cars in Canada in its first year, the U.S. auto market is about eleven times as big as the Canadian, and if we get around 50% of this sales level here, this would be a success," he said.   Penske said he received 1,100 applications from interested dealers for a possible franchises. From these applicants, UAG will choose between 50 and 60 dealers for the brand's launch in the U.S., Penske said, adding that the company will go on a roadshow to Las Vegas, Atlanta, Detroit and New York over the next 30 days.   Penske reiterated that the Smart Fortwo will go on sale for "a price below $15,000".     Company Web site: http://www.daimlerchrysler.com     -By Christoph Rauwald, Dow Jones Newswires; +49 69 29 725 512; christoph.rauwald@dowjones.com  -0-   APDJ-01-07-07 1951GMT<   (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 15:00 ET (20:00 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: Colombia's Gilinskis Seek Control Of Bancolombia -Report
Story: BOGOTA (Dow Jones)--Isaac Gilinski, a Colombian businessman whose family formerly owned Banco de Colombia SA, said he wants to get control of the country's biggest bank Bancolombia SA (CIB), the newspaper El Tiempo reported Sunday.   The Gilinski family, who sold control of Banco de Colombia SA to Banco Industrial Colombiano in 1997 for $418 million, sued BIC claiming the family was defrauded by BIC executives.   The merged bank was renamed Bancolombia.   "The only friendly solution is for them to pay the 1.5 trillion Colombian pesos ($673 million) the experts hired by the prosecutor said we are entitled to," El Tiempo quoted Gilinski as saying. "I think they have to give us the bank back."   The family's lawyers said the family originally sought $632 million in damages. None of Gilinski's lawyers were immediately available for comment Sunday.   The Gilinskis owns several businesses in Colombia, Central America and the U.S. They control the Colombian bank Banco GNB Sudameris.   As part of the lawsuit, a public prosecutor Thursday ordered Bancolombia's Chief Executive Jorge Londono and the bank's vice president Federico Ochoa to be placed under house arrest.   When BIC bought 51% of Banco de Colombia, it financed the purchase with loans from its Panamanian unit that were then transferred onto the books of the newly merged entity, the prosecutor said. BIC also failed to inject $58 million promised in equity for the new bank as part of the transaction.   The prosecutor accused the two executives of fraud, unlawful use of public funds and non-authorized operations with shareholders, according to a statement from the chief prosecutor's office.   The 10-year-old dispute was reopened in October 2006 after the Gilisnki family, which lost an initial decision, appealed to the country's Constitutional Court.   In a statement e-mailed late Friday, Bancolombia said the bank and its officers acted "with the highest degree of loyalty and transparency" and that the process followed all the legal requirements.   "Neither Bancolombia nor its officers have made improper use of public funds, nor have they appropriated any such funds," the statement said.   Londono denies any wrongdoing and will challenge the prosecutor's decision, according to his attorney, Ricardo Calvete.   Calvete said his client has not been notified of the arrest order yet, and so is not confined to his home.   According to Calvete, Londono is still Bancolombia's CEO.   Bancolombia's ADR fell 6.2% on Thursday after the news of the arrest order broke off, though the price partly recovered on Friday, gaining 1.3% to end at $30.39. The New York-traded share will resume trading Monday.   The locally traded share of Bancolombia fell 4.6% on Friday to COP16,480, while the share of the holding company controlling the bank Suramericana de Inversiones SA (SURAMINV.BO) fell 3% to COP19,500.   The stocks are the two most liquid shares of the local stock exchange, and account for about 17% of the total market capitalization of the exchange.   Monday is a holiday in Colombia, so the shares will only resume trading Tuesday.     -By Inti Landauro, Dow Jones Newswires; 57-310-867 6542; colombia@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 15:30 ET (20:30 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK: Home Cooking At Chrysler
Story: Edited by Paul Vigna     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES       (call: 201-938-5172; email: paul.vigna@dowjones.com)       AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK can be found using N/DJMT and I/AUT     1:26 (Dow Jones) In the minutes leading up to Chrysler Group's big auto show press conference, there were giant loafs of bread flanking the stage. A kitchen counter was in the middle, as if on a cooking show. Irreverent slices of cartoon bread danced on a giant screen.   What was the theme for this revamped minivan unveiling event - the "best thing since sliced bread" or "something's cooking at Chrysler"? Nope. Instead, it was Chrysler Group's focus on its "bread and butter" vehicles. The DaimlerChrysler AG (DCX) unit rolled out the latest versions of its Dodge Caravan and Chrysler Town & Country minivans, replete with a host of gadgets and options. Not listed: the wood paneling seen on the old Plymouth Voyager minivan, also rolled out as Chrysler touted it's long pioneering position in the vehicle segment.   Chrysler President Tom LaSorda was joined on stage by celebrity chef Bobby Flay, and the two made a couple of quick dishes that represent the Chrysler and Dodge brands - spicy pork loin with mango for Dodge and a smooth chocolate ganache cake for Chrysler.   When LaSorda took a turn icing the cake, Flay told the executive, "I can tell you've spent a lot of time in the hot kitchen," to which LaSorda replied, "The kitchen's been pretty hot lately, I'll tell you," a reference to Chrysler's tough 2006. (JDK, TKS)   1:08 (Dow Jones) Ford's (F) new leader, Alan Mulally, looked like a lifer in his appearance at the company's press conference. Driven out in a glistening new 500 sedan, Mulally was poised and energetic in discussing Ford's cars and prospects, sounding much like a man who's excited about what he's doing. After the event, North American head Mark Fields - who matched Mulally in the enthusiasm department - said he expects the auto maker's sales will be down slightly, with light vehicle sales of roughly 16.4M, as the US economy slows down. Fields expects GDP of 2%-2.5%, with a moderating job market and weak housing market. (PJV)   12:40 (Dow Jones) Was that a press conference or a rock concert? Ford's (F) flashy press conference featured deafening rock music, a light show and five giant video screens. Executives like Bill Ford Jr. and Mark Fields were driven onto the stage in glistening cars and greeted like guitar heroes. The music was so loud it drowned out the engine on Ford's concept muscle car, the Interceptor. Even Bill Gates was trotted out via satellite to talk about Ford and Microsoft's (MSFT) "Sync" project. 2006 was difficult, Bill Ford said, and 2007 will be pivotal, but the company's laid the foundation for a better Ford. (PJV)   11:05 (Dow Jones) Johnson Control (JCI) is trying to beef up the gadget-connection capability in cars, an issue in the spotlight at this year's North American International Auto Show with the Ford/Microsoft deal. JCI on Sunday unveiled its Mobile Device Gateway, which would allow drivers to use Bluetooth, USB and serial ports to plug in cell phones, MP3 players and other devices and use them as if they were factory-installed. JCI is working with automakers on making it available in 2010 and "maybe even a little earlier," says Scott Wright, vice president of electronic sales and marketing. The system expands on JCI's current Bluetooth system. (TAK)   10:53 (Dow Jones) The media are descending on Detroit. The centennial North American auto show kicks off today, with a full slate of events and hoards of journalists jockeying for position. GM is building the early buzz, with its glitzy runway show last night and its fairly surprising sweep of the North American car and truck awards this morning. The company also has a noon press conference where it will unveil its latest concept car, the Chevy Volt, and talk about getting back into the electric car market - just as soon as it develops a new type of battery. (PJV)     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 13:26 ET (18:26 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK: High Voltage, Smart Cars In Detroit
Story: Edited by Paul Vigna     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES       (call: 201-938-5172; email: paul.vigna@dowjones.com)       AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK can be found using N/DJMT and I/AUT     5:19 (Dow Jones) The centennial North American International Auto Show kicked off today at Cobo Hall in Detroit, and from a car so advanced General Motors (GM) can't even produce it yet - the Chevy Volt - to a car so small it can fit in a phone booth - the Smart ForTwo - the show has produced more than enough to keep car enthusiasts, investors and even journalists busy. The press preview runs through Monday, then industry insiders get their look, and on the 13th it opens to the public. What follows are some of the first day's highlights. (PJV)   5:06 (Dow Jones) Without a doubt, some of the most beautiful and powerful cars at the auto show in Detroit are from the House of Sant'Agata Bolognese - Lamborghini. At the decidedly high end of the auto market, Lamborghini has three models on display, the Murcielago LP640 Roadster, the Murcielago LP640 Coupe and the Gallardo Spyder. The Italian luxury auto maker also reported at the show that 2006 was a record year, with 2,087 cars built and sold, up 30.4% from a year ago. The 640 Roadster, first introduced at the Los Angeles auto show in November, will go on sale in the spring. The cost? Roughly $400,000. (PJV)   4:13 (Dow Jones) One of if not the smallest cars here is the Smart car, a DaimlerChrysler (DCX) product that's been popular in Europe and will make its US debut in the 1Q08, being sold through United Auto Group (UAG). The little car - it's being displayed outside Cobo Hall maneuvering through and parking between limos and could almost fit in the bed of a Silverado - is being introduced at the "right time," UAG CEO Roger Penske says. Penske wouldn't make a production estimate, but did say jokingly it would be in the "double digits." Penske was asked how he would reply to potential customers worried about driving such a small car on US roads alongside all those big SUVs. He said the car is small, but it's high-tech and has a plethora of safety features. "It's amazing how resilient it is because of the design." (PJV)   3:52 (Dow Jones) With all the high-tech, space-age know-how on display, it was an usual sight to see a man standing in the lobby of Cobo Hall next to one of the lowest tech vehicles around: a sled. A team of five barking, yelping huskies was attached to the sled, and they ran into the main hall and onto DaimlerChrysler's (DCX) exhibit space, which was covered in a sheet of ice, to kick off DCX's presentation. DCX introduced several new models with its 4matic drive - the general theme being 4matic can handle any terrain - and a few with its Bluetec, clean diesel engines. The dogs were followed by hockey players and ice skaters. "I hope you didn't expect to see me on skates," CEO Dr. Dieter Zetsche said. (PJV)   3:25 (Dow Jones) GM CEO Rick Wagoner says the Chevy Volt electric car "isn't about science projects." The auto maker has set aside hundreds of millions of dollars to get the electric car started, but Wagoner indicates the company will spend significantly more than $500M to make it a reality. Wagoner says the company needs to build more than the 1,000 or so electric cars the company did in its last electric car effort, the abandoned EV1 program, and adds their vision is clearer this time. Instead, GM would ideally like to build "hundreds of thousands, (even) millions a year...this is an opportunity to deliver results." He concedes, however, there are question marks around the technology. "Production time will depend on development of battery technology," he says. (JDS/PI)   2:16 (Dow Jones) GM Vice Chairman Bob Lutz called it an "inconvenient truth" that his company has indeed started development of a new "E-Flex" vehicle, the Chevrolet Volt, which run on electricity as well as biodiesel, ethanol and, yes, gasoline. The Volt has a sporty look, WSJ.com observes, and Lutz noted an electric vehicle can also "look good." The Volt can drive 40 miles before other fuels need to help recharge and Lutz emphasized that 78% of Americans live within 20 miles of work. He said if someone drove to work, ran nearby errands and charged the car every night, the owner would never have to buy gasoline for the lifetime of the vehicle, he said. For now, though, the Volt remains only an intriguing concept. (MS)   (http://blogs.wsj.com/autoshow/)   1:26 (Dow Jones) In the minutes leading up to Chrysler Group's big auto show press conference, there were giant loafs of bread flanking the stage. A kitchen counter was in the middle, as if on a cooking show. Irreverent slices of cartoon bread danced on a giant screen.   What was the theme for this revamped minivan unveiling event - the "best thing since sliced bread" or "something's cooking at Chrysler"? Nope. Instead, it was Chrysler Group's focus on its "bread and butter" vehicles. The DaimlerChrysler AG (DCX) unit rolled out the latest versions of its Dodge Caravan and Chrysler Town & Country minivans, replete with a host of gadgets and options. Not listed: the wood paneling seen on the old Plymouth Voyager minivan, also rolled out as Chrysler touted it's long pioneering position in the vehicle segment.   Chrysler President Tom LaSorda was joined on stage by celebrity chef Bobby Flay, and the two made a couple of quick dishes that represent the Chrysler and Dodge brands - spicy pork loin with mango for Dodge and a smooth chocolate ganache cake for Chrysler.   When LaSorda took a turn icing the cake, Flay told the executive, "I can tell you've spent a lot of time in the hot kitchen," to which LaSorda replied, "The kitchen's been pretty hot lately, I'll tell you," a reference to Chrysler's tough 2006. (JDK, TKS)   1:08 (Dow Jones) Ford's (F) new leader, Alan Mulally, looked like a lifer in his appearance at the company's press conference. Driven out in a glistening new 500 sedan, Mulally was poised and energetic in discussing Ford's cars and prospects, sounding much like a man who's excited about what he's doing. After the event, North American head Mark Fields - who matched Mulally in the enthusiasm department - said he expects the auto maker's sales will be down slightly, with light vehicle sales of roughly 16.4M, as the US economy slows down. Fields expects GDP of 2%-2.5%, with a moderating job market and weak housing market. (PJV)   12:40 (Dow Jones) Was that a press conference or a rock concert? Ford's (F) flashy press conference featured deafening rock music, a light show and five giant video screens. Executives like Bill Ford Jr. and Mark Fields were driven onto the stage in glistening cars and greeted like guitar heroes. The music was so loud it drowned out the engine on Ford's concept muscle car, the Interceptor. Even Bill Gates was trotted out via satellite to talk about Ford and Microsoft's (MSFT) "Sync" project. 2006 was difficult, Bill Ford said, and 2007 will be pivotal, but the company's laid the foundation for a better Ford. (PJV)   11:05 (Dow Jones) Johnson Control (JCI) is trying to beef up the gadget-connection capability in cars, an issue in the spotlight at this year's North American International Auto Show with the Ford/Microsoft deal. JCI on Sunday unveiled its Mobile Device Gateway, which would allow drivers to use Bluetooth, USB and serial ports to plug in cell phones, MP3 players and other devices and use them as if they were factory-installed. JCI is working with automakers on making it available in 2010 and "maybe even a little earlier," says Scott Wright, vice president of electronic sales and marketing. The system expands on JCI's current Bluetooth system. (TAK)   10:53 (Dow Jones) The media are descending on Detroit. The centennial North American auto show kicks off today, with a full slate of events and hoards of journalists jockeying for position. GM is building the early buzz, with its glitzy runway show last night and its fairly surprising sweep of the North American car and truck awards this morning. The company also has a noon press conference where it will unveil its latest concept car, the Chevy Volt, and talk about getting back into the electric car market - just as soon as it develops a new type of battery. (PJV)     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 17:19 ET (22:19 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.
