Headline: : NBC Universal Teams Up With MediaFLO USA to Bring the Best in Live News and Entertainment Programming to Mobile Users
Story: - Top NBCU Content to be Offered, Including 'Today,' 'Nightly News with Brian Williams,' 'Meet the Press,' 'Late Night with Conan O'Brien' and 'The Tonight Show with Jay Leno' -       SAN DIEGO, Jan. 7 /PRNewswire-FirstCall/ -- MediaFLO(TM) USA Inc., a wholly owned subsidiary of QUALCOMM Incorporated (Nasdaq: QCOM), today announced a multi-year agreement to license premium entertainment and news channels from NBC Universal for its TV-quality, mobile entertainment service. With this agreement, MediaFLO USA intends to bring consumers live, 24/7 access to select NBC Universal programming on two of the service's dedicated channels.     Through MediaFLO USA's service, consumers will be able to view, in the palm of their hands, both the unparalleled news and information coverage of NBC News and some of NBC Universal's best known entertainment programming. The news channel will feature live, full-length programs, including "Today," "Nightly News with Brian Williams" and "Meet the Press," as well as select programming from both MSNBC and CNBC.  On the entertainment front, the channel will offer a select number of acclaimed NBC Universal primetime, daytime and cable shows, as well as access to the best late-night entertainment laughs around, including "The Tonight Show with Jay Leno" and "Late Night with Conan O'Brien."     "We are very excited to offer a linear, high-quality, full-length content experience to an audience of engaged consumers on the go," said George Kliavkoff, chief digital officer, NBC Universal.  "Our partnership with MediaFLO USA allows us to present some of our rich entertainment and news programming in a way that has never before been available on mobile.  NBC Universal will continue to develop innovative offerings, including targeting local programming and services with our affiliate partners, as the capabilities become available."     "NBC Universal has earned a reputation for creating imaginative programming and finding innovative new ways to deliver it," said Paul Jacobs, chief executive officer, QUALCOMM.  "In partnership with NBC, MediaFLO USA will extend the TV experience into a fully mobile environment."     "MediaFLO USA is revolutionizing television by offering viewers an entirely new way to enjoy popular entertainment and news programming," said Gina Lombardi, president of MediaFLO USA.  "The alliance of NBC Universal's content and MediaFLO USA's TV-quality video, intuitive program guide and fast switching between programs creates a mobile entertainment experience unlike any other."     MediaFLO USA is creating an unmatched mobile entertainment experience, delivering premium content directly to subscribers' mobile phones in partnership with wireless operators.  Guided by extensive market research and consumer trials, MediaFLO USA is securing familiar, premium content from many of the world's leading media companies and leveraging its dedicated, nationwide multicast network to deliver live, full-length programming to mobile phones at TV quality.     NBC Universal is one of the world's leading media and entertainment companies in the development, production and marketing of entertainment, news and information to a global audience.  Formed in May 2004 through the combining of NBC and Vivendi Universal Entertainment, NBC Universal owns and operates a valuable portfolio of news and entertainment networks, a premier motion picture company, significant television production operations, a leading television stations group and world-renowned theme parks.  NBC Universal is 80 percent-owned by General Electric, with 20 percent controlled by Vivendi Universal.     MediaFLO USA Inc. aggregates and intends to deliver premium, TV-quality entertainment and information services to mobile phones over its dedicated nationwide wireless network.  Offering an unprecedented combination of full-length programming, short-format clips and realtime information and entertainment feeds, MediaFLO USA will deliver a uniquely compelling mobile viewing experience.  MediaFLO USA intends to partner with world-class content providers, wireless operators and advertisers to make its service available to U.S. consumers in the first quarter of 2007.  Based in San Diego, Calif., MediaFLO USA is a subsidiary of QUALCOMM Incorporated.     Except for the historical information contained herein, this news release contains forward-looking statements that are subject to risks and uncertainties, including the ability of MediaFLO USA to form timely and profitable partnerships with content providers, wireless operators and advertisers, the extent and speed to which FLO technology and the MediaFLO USA Inc. network are deployed, the extent and speed of adoption by consumers of MediaFLO USA's service, the speed with which NBC Universal programming is integrated into the MediaFLO service package, change in economic conditions of the various markets MediaFLO USA serves, as well as the other risks detailed from time to time in QUALCOMM's SEC reports, including the report on Form 10-K for the year ended September 24, 2006, and most recent Form 10-Q.     QUALCOMM is a registered trademark of QUALCOMM Incorporated.  MediaFLO and FLO are trademarks of QUALCOMM Incorporated.  All other trademarks are the property of their respective owners.          QUALCOMM Contacts:      Julie Reynolds, MediaFLO USA Inc.      Phone:  1-858-845-3516      Email:  julier@qualcomm.com        Kristin Atkins, Corporate Communications      Phone:  1-858-845-5959      Email:  corpcomm@qualcomm.com        Garrett Ponder, Investor Relations      Phone:  1-858-658-4813      Email:  ir@qualcomm.com        NBC Universal Contacts:      Alyssa Donelan, NBC Universal Cable Communications      Phone:  1-201-735-3568      Email:  alyssa.donelan@nbcuni.com        Allison Gollust, NBC News Communications      Phone:  1-212-664-3220      Email:  allison.gollust@nbcuni.com        Joe Libonati, NBC Universal Television Group Publicity      Phone:  1-818-840-3050      Email:  joe.libonati@nbcuni.com        Amy Zelvin, NBC Universal Digital Media Communications      Phone:  1-212-664-7436      Email:  amy.zelvin@nbcuni.com      SOURCE  MediaFLO USA Inc.       /CONTACT: Julie Reynolds of MediaFLO USA Inc., +1-858-845-3516, julier@qualcomm.com; or Kristin Atkins, Corporate Communications, +1-858-845-5959, corpcomm@qualcomm.com, or Garrett Ponder, Investor Relations, +1-858-658-4813, ir@qualcomm.com, both of QUALCOMM Incorporated; or Alyssa Donelan, NBC Universal Cable Communications, +1-201-735-3568, alyssa.donelan@nbcuni.com; or Allison Gollust, NBC News Communications, +1-212-664-3220, allison.gollust@nbcuni.com; or Joe Libonati, NBC Universal Television Group Publicity, +1-818-840-3050, joe.libonati@nbcuni.com; or Amy Zelvin, NBC Universal Digital Media Communications, +1-212-664-7436, amy.zelvin@nbcuni.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 16:00 ET (21:00 GMT)

Headline: : 2008 Ford Five Hundred Offers More Style, Power and Standard Safety Features
Story: DETROIT, Jan. 7 /PRNewswire-FirstCall/ -- The Ford Five Hundred sedan packs nearly 30 percent more power and boasts a new look inside and out for the 2008 model year.     On sale by summer 2007, the Five Hundred features a new front end resembling the popular Ford Fusion, more horsepower and torque thanks to a new 3.5-liter V-6 engine, a new six-speed transmission and all-wheel-drive system and safety upgrades that include Ford's available AdvanceTrac(R) electronic stability control system. Structural upgrades to further improve crash protection include reinforcements in the footwell area and new interior door panels.     "Customers love the Five Hundred's ride and package, and its safety reputation is excellent," says Cisco Codina, Ford's group vice president of North America Marketing, Sales and Service. "For this year, we've dialed up the appeal with a new, more expressive look, a more powerful engine and more than 500 changes to make this great car even better."     The Five Hundred's 3.5-liter Duratec V-6 now delivers an estimated 260 horsepower and 245 pound-feet of torque. It also benefits from the same smooth shifting, six-speed automatic transmission and the same available all-wheel- drive system as the new Ford Edge. Importantly, even with the upgraded powertrain, real-world fuel economy for the front-wheel-drive model is expected to be similar to the current model -- thanks to advancements in powertrain technology.        New look inside and out     The Five Hundred's new look aligns it with the Ford Fusion. New from the A-pillars forward, the Five Hundred now features Ford's signature three-bar chrome grille. A sculpted hood adds a touch of crisp detail, and a new front fascia is chamfered at the outer edges, adding structure to the design.  All- new side mirrors are smaller yet provide better visibility and reduce wind noise. Chrome side vents, door handles and mirror caps give the Five Hundred Limited models a more expensive appearance. New taillamps carry the horizontal theme to the rear, while a new rear fascia houses chrome-tipped dual exhausts.        Ultra-quiet interior and plush ride     For 2008, the Five Hundred's sound package has been completely revised, helping make it as quiet as many luxury cars. The new sound package includes such technologies as expandable foam pellets in the A-pillars to reduce wind noise and the use of an advanced sound-deadening material called Sonosorb(TM) in the doors, headliner and pillars. Sonosorb increases sound-deadening efficiency by 20 percent while retaining the same thickness as the material it replaces.     Engineers also reduced road noise by stiffening the area where the rear package shelf meets the floor pan. Even the climate control system was improved by making the system 50 percent quieter than before.     The Five Hundred's quiet, confident ride starts with an already solid foundation. Upgrades include revised shock towers that help increase front suspension travel by 10 percent, new dampers and springs in both front and rear, and a revised, retuned rear suspension.     One of the most significant changes is how the engine is mounted in the vehicle. Previously, the engine was mounted to the front subframe. On the new model, the engine and transmission are bolted to the body with hydraulic mounts to reduce vibration. By moving the roughly 600-pound powerpack off the subframe, engineers were able to better tune the suspension and, ultimately, create an even better ride.        Maximum convenience and space     The Five Hundred features the most spacious interior of any large sedan, with best-in-class legroom front and rear and 60/40-split fold-flat second-row seats. With the fold-flat front-passenger seat, items up to nine-feet long can fit inside.     Five Hundred also offers a number of must-have technologies. In addition to a standard auxiliary audio input jack, available convenience features include a voice-activated navigation system, a DVD entertainment system and factory-installed SIRIUS(R) satellite radio. Ford Sync(TM) is also available on the new Five Hundred. Sync is a voice-activated hands-free in-car communications and entertainment system which fully-integrates mobile phones and digital media players. The Sync in-car communications system was developed in collaboration with Microsoft and will be offered exclusively on 12 Ford, Lincoln and Mercury products in North America beginning this year.        Building on safety leadership     The 2007 Five Hundred is already the segment leader in safety, earning five stars in all four categories for the U.S. government's crash tests. Five Hundred was also the first Gold Award winner from the Insurance Institute for Highway Safety (IIHS) and is the class leader in rear crash performance.     For 2008, Five Hundred offers the added safety and control of Ford's AdvanceTrac(R) electronic stability control system. AdvanceTrac can predict the vehicle's intentions using a sensor to detect and measure oversteer and yaw by monitoring the vehicle's speed, throttle position and steering wheel angle. When the system senses wheel slip, engine torque is reduced and braking is applied where needed to help keep the car tracking safely on its intended path.     Five Hundred comes standard with dual-stage driver and passenger front air bags, seat-deployed side air bags for driver and front passenger and Safety Canopy(TM) side curtain rollover air bags for both rows.        About Ford Motor Company     Ford Motor Company, a global automotive industry leader based in Dearborn, Mich., manufactures and distributes automobiles in 200 markets across six continents. With about 300,000 employees and more than 100 plants worldwide, the company's core and affiliated automotive brands include Aston Martin, Ford, Jaguar, Land Rover, Lincoln, Mazda, Mercury and Volvo. Its automotive- related services include Ford Motor Credit Company. For more information regarding Ford's products, please visit http://www.fordvehicles.com.        Additional media information is available at http://www.media.ford.com.    SOURCE  Ford Motor Company       /CONTACT: Afaf Farah, +1-313-845-0307, afarah@ford.com, Alan Hall, +1-313-594-3744, ahall32@ford.com, Mark Schirmer, +1-313-390-8647, mschirme@ford.com, all of Ford Motor Company      /Web site: http://www.ford.com      /Web site: http://www.fordvehicles.com      /Web site: http://www.media.ford.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 00:01 ET (05:01 GMT)

Headline: UK PRESS: Doubts Over Essar's Right Of Refusal
Story: LONDON (Dow Jones)--A document filed in the U.S. throws into doubt claims that Essar Group has first right of refusal over any bid for Hutchison Essar, according to a report in the weekend edition of the Financial Times.   This would potentially remove a hurdle for Vodafone PLC (VOD), the Hinduja Group or other parties in the battle for India's fourth-largest mobile company.   The internal document was filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission in 2004, the report said. Vodafone declined to comment; Essar Group could not be reached for comment.     Newspaper Web site: http://www.ft.com   -London Bureau, Dow Jones Newswires; +44 (0)20 7842 9320     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 06:01 ET (11:01 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: UK PRESS: Tesco May Be Forced To Sell Off Land Bank
Story: LONDON (Dow Jones)--Tesco PLC (TSCO.LN), the U.K. supermarket chain, could be forced to sell its land bank under proposals being pushed by members of a Competition Commission review into supermarkets, the Sunday Telegraph reported, citing unnamed people familiar with the deliberations.   The report said that at least two of the six panel members are arguing that Tesco's vast unused property portfolio stymies rivals from entering local markets.   The newspaper quoted a Tesco spokesman as saying: "The land that we have is essentially a pipeline of new stores and that's the only reason we hold it." He added other supermarkets have similar land banks, though he acknowledged Tesco has the largest.     Newspaper Web site: http://www.telegraph.co.uk     -London Bureau, Dow Jones Newswires; +44 (0)20 7842 9320     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 08:09 ET (13:09 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK: Mush!
Story: Edited by Paul Vigna     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES       (call: 201-938-5172; email: paul.vigna@dowjones.com)       AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK can be found using N/DJMT and I/AUT     3:52 (Dow Jones) With all the high-tech, space-age know-how on display, it was an usual sight to see a man standing in the lobby of Cobo Hall next to one of the lowest tech vehicles around: a sled. A team of five barking, yelping huskies was attached to the sled, and they ran into the main hall and onto DaimlerChrysler's (DCX) exhibit space, which was covered in a sheet of ice, to kick off DCX's presentation. DCX introduced several new models with its 4matic drive - the general theme being 4matic can handle any terrain - and a few with its Bluetec, clean diesel engines. The dogs were followed by hockey players and ice skaters. "I hope you didn't expect to see me on skates," CEO Dr. Dieter Zetsche said. (PJV)   3:25 (Dow Jones) GM CEO Rick Wagoner says the Chevy Volt electric car "isn't about science projects." The auto maker has set aside hundreds of millions of dollars to get the electric car started, but Wagoner indicates the company will spend significantly more than $500M to make it a reality. Wagoner says the company needs to build more than the 1,000 or so electric cars the company did in its last electric car effort, the abandoned EV1 program, and adds their vision is clearer this time. Instead, GM would ideally like to build "hundreds of thousands, (even) millions a year...this is an opportunity to deliver results." He concedes, however, there are question marks around the technology. "Production time will depend on development of battery technology," he says. (JDS/PI)   2:16 (Dow Jones) GM Vice Chairman Bob Lutz called it an "inconvenient truth" that his company has indeed started development of a new "E-Flex" vehicle, the Chevrolet Volt, which run on electricity as well as biodiesel, ethanol and, yes, gasoline. The Volt has a sporty look, WSJ.com observes, and Lutz noted an electric vehicle can also "look good." The Volt can drive 40 miles before other fuels need to help recharge and Lutz emphasized that 78% of Americans live within 20 miles of work. He said if someone drove to work, ran nearby errands and charged the car every night, the owner would never have to buy gasoline for the lifetime of the vehicle, he said. For now, though, the Volt remains only an intriguing concept. (MS)   (http://blogs.wsj.com/autoshow/)   1:26 (Dow Jones) In the minutes leading up to Chrysler Group's big auto show press conference, there were giant loafs of bread flanking the stage. A kitchen counter was in the middle, as if on a cooking show. Irreverent slices of cartoon bread danced on a giant screen.   What was the theme for this revamped minivan unveiling event - the "best thing since sliced bread" or "something's cooking at Chrysler"? Nope. Instead, it was Chrysler Group's focus on its "bread and butter" vehicles. The DaimlerChrysler AG (DCX) unit rolled out the latest versions of its Dodge Caravan and Chrysler Town & Country minivans, replete with a host of gadgets and options. Not listed: the wood paneling seen on the old Plymouth Voyager minivan, also rolled out as Chrysler touted it's long pioneering position in the vehicle segment.   Chrysler President Tom LaSorda was joined on stage by celebrity chef Bobby Flay, and the two made a couple of quick dishes that represent the Chrysler and Dodge brands - spicy pork loin with mango for Dodge and a smooth chocolate ganache cake for Chrysler.   When LaSorda took a turn icing the cake, Flay told the executive, "I can tell you've spent a lot of time in the hot kitchen," to which LaSorda replied, "The kitchen's been pretty hot lately, I'll tell you," a reference to Chrysler's tough 2006. (JDK, TKS)   1:08 (Dow Jones) Ford's (F) new leader, Alan Mulally, looked like a lifer in his appearance at the company's press conference. Driven out in a glistening new 500 sedan, Mulally was poised and energetic in discussing Ford's cars and prospects, sounding much like a man who's excited about what he's doing. After the event, North American head Mark Fields - who matched Mulally in the enthusiasm department - said he expects the auto maker's sales will be down slightly, with light vehicle sales of roughly 16.4M, as the US economy slows down. Fields expects GDP of 2%-2.5%, with a moderating job market and weak housing market. (PJV)   12:40 (Dow Jones) Was that a press conference or a rock concert? Ford's (F) flashy press conference featured deafening rock music, a light show and five giant video screens. Executives like Bill Ford Jr. and Mark Fields were driven onto the stage in glistening cars and greeted like guitar heroes. The music was so loud it drowned out the engine on Ford's concept muscle car, the Interceptor. Even Bill Gates was trotted out via satellite to talk about Ford and Microsoft's (MSFT) "Sync" project. 2006 was difficult, Bill Ford said, and 2007 will be pivotal, but the company's laid the foundation for a better Ford. (PJV)   11:05 (Dow Jones) Johnson Control (JCI) is trying to beef up the gadget-connection capability in cars, an issue in the spotlight at this year's North American International Auto Show with the Ford/Microsoft deal. JCI on Sunday unveiled its Mobile Device Gateway, which would allow drivers to use Bluetooth, USB and serial ports to plug in cell phones, MP3 players and other devices and use them as if they were factory-installed. JCI is working with automakers on making it available in 2010 and "maybe even a little earlier," says Scott Wright, vice president of electronic sales and marketing. The system expands on JCI's current Bluetooth system. (TAK)   10:53 (Dow Jones) The media are descending on Detroit. The centennial North American auto show kicks off today, with a full slate of events and hoards of journalists jockeying for position. GM is building the early buzz, with its glitzy runway show last night and its fairly surprising sweep of the North American car and truck awards this morning. The company also has a noon press conference where it will unveil its latest concept car, the Chevy Volt, and talk about getting back into the electric car market - just as soon as it develops a new type of battery. (PJV)     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 15:52 ET (20:52 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: =WSJ: LaSorda: Chrysler Reining In Excess Inventory
Story: By Neal E. Boudette     of the WALL STREET JOURNAL     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--DaimlerChrysler AG's Chrysler Group has trimmed its stock of "unassigned" vehicles to fewer than 10,000, Chrysler Chief Executive Tom LaSorda said in an interview Sunday.   Chrysler was stuck with bloated inventories last year after building cars and trucks that had not been ordered by dealers. In September it had about 100,000 of these unassigned vehicles.   But Chrysler executives at the North American International Auto Show said the company has its inventory situation under control. Mr. Lasorda said Chrysler's main inventory, which does not include unassigned vehicles, is now 538,000 cars and trucks, down from 597,000 at the end of 2005.     (This story and related background material will be available on The Wall Street Journal Web site, WSJ.com.)   Chrysler had an operating loss of $1.5 billion in the third quarter, although parent DaimlerChrysler remained profitable, thanks to a strong showing by its Mercedes-Benz luxury division. Mr. LaSorda is supposed to unveil a restructuring plan by the end of February to cut costs and put the division back into the black.   Mr. LaSorda said he has the "full support" of DaimlerChrysler Chief Executive Dieter Zetsche to give the restructuring plan a chance to work.   Cutting Chrysler's inventory is a key part of rebuilding profitability, however. In a separate interview, sales head Steve Landry acknowledged the auto maker still has not cut stocks to the levels it is aiming for.   To help boost sales of pickup trucks amid increasing competition, Chrysler plans to offer its V-8 Hemi engine in Ram pickups at no additional cost to customers, Mr. Landry acknowledged.   Chrysler had planned to roll out the offer in March but is now considering starting it sooner. The planned Hemi promotion was first reported by the Detroit News last week.   The Hemi deal marks a dramatic turnaround from 2005,  when gas prices were lower and customers were paying about $5,000 extra to get Hemi-equipped models.   -By Neal E. Boudette, The Wall Street Journal; 313-226-1256, Neal.Bourdette@wsj.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 16:30 ET (21:30 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: : Two American Icons Deliver the Crossover Model of the Future With the Ford Airstream Concept
Story: * Crossover growth is exploding: Ford Airstream Concept speaks to the future of crossovers as the market segment is projected to top 3 million units annually by the end of the decade. * Green Journey: Ford Airstream Concept is powered by a new plug-in hydrogen hybrid fuel cell - called HySeries Drive - that operates under electric power at all times and delivers the combined city/highway equivalent fuel economy of 41 miles per gallon. * Two icons of American transportation: Ford and Airstream have teamed up to deliver a futuristic crossover concept, showing what tomorrow's road trip vehicles could look like.       DETROIT, Jan. 7 /PRNewswire-FirstCall/ -- Playing to win in the growing crossover segment, Ford has joined with another iconic company to showcase how it could further expand its lineup of expressive crossovers with the Ford Airstream Concept.     "Crossovers are an increasingly important part of our business, and Ford is going to continue developing an expressive range of these vehicles," says Peter Horbury, executive director - Design, The Americas.  "The Ford Airstream Concept is a futuristic look at crossovers.  It's the ultimate modern touring vehicle that delivers flexibility and capability with dynamic design that evokes the spirit of the journey."     The concept is powered by a plug-in hydrogen hybrid fuel cell drivetrain -- called HySeries Drive(TM) -- that operates under electric power at all times.  This advanced fuel cell system is half the weight and cost of today's fuel cells and can operate in the dead of winter.  That's a major step forward because today's fuel cells don't do well when the mercury dips below freezing.        Natural Intersection     The Ford Airstream Concept captures the sense of optimism and adventure conveyed in American aircraft, spacecraft and the streamlined shape of Airstream trailers.  It's reflected in the crossover concept's organic, fuselage-inspired form language, unique reflective paint and 12 ceremonial rivets, which pay homage to Airstream's iconic construction.     "For 75 years, Airstream has been an icon synonymous with the optimism, discovery and wanderlust that's helped defined America," said J Mays, group vice president - Design, and chief creative officer.  "It seemed only fitting for us to come together through our shared passion for the open road and show a vision for the future of American transportation."     Much like Ford, Airstream began with one man's dream.  In 1931, Wally Byam began leveraging aircraft-construction methods to make trailers aimed at feeding Americans' surging desire to travel.     "Silver bullets" have been shooting up and down highways ever since, leading a Recreational Vehicle industry that's realized record profits and revenues in 2005 and the first half of 2006.     "Business for Airstream and the RV industry has been strong, but we want to continue finding options for tomorrow's road trips.  Our success in recent years has come from challenging the conventional thinking about what an Airstream is.  The Ford Airstream Concept is a stunning example of just that," says Bob Wheeler, president and chief executive officer of Airstream.  "Plus, a partner like Ford, with its long history as an American icon, made perfect sense for this kind of exploration."        Common Ground     Both companies are influenced by economic and demographic trends -- chiefly baby boomers approaching retirement age.     In the U.S., 11,000 people turn age 50 every day.  These consumers are starting to downsize their lives and their vehicles, opting for more nimble and fuel-efficient models.  With their children leaving home and some retiring, they also have more time for travel.     For Ford, that trend -- plus younger couples starting families later -- is fueling a shift to crossover vehicles.     The crossover segment is expected to hit 3 million units by the end of the decade, making it potentially the largest U.S. vehicle segment.     For Airstream, these demographic changes are meaningful as well. RV ownership is highest among retirement-age consumers, and by the end of the decade, 50- to 64-year-old consumers will tally 57 million -- a 38 percent increase versus 2000, according to University of Michigan studies.  And the number of RV-owning households is expected to grow to 8.5 million during the same period.        Seeing the Future Today     Growing Ford's crossover share means breaking through the competitive and fragmenting segment, and the company is leveraging bold designs to win customers.     Ford's crossover lineup already features the functional Freestyle, newly launched agile and modern Edge and, in time, will include a more refined full-size crossover based on the Fairlane concept.     Ford designers wanted to push further into the future and tapped inspirations including Airstream's iconic designs and the optimistic future Stanley Kubrick created and captured in his 1960s cult film 2001: A Space Odyssey.  These inspirations are evident -- inside and out.     The concept's bold, futuristic front-end explores a new look for Ford, encapsulating the single-surface grille and headlamps into the same graphic. Each of the concept's bold orange-trimmed window graphics is a unique shape.     "This reflects the purpose of the vehicle:  looking out and remembering that the journey -- not the destination -- matters most," said Freeman Thomas, director, North American Strategic Design.  "The Ford Airstream Concept is an ultra-modern, optimistic vehicle that allows passengers a pure traveling experience to enjoy with good company, no matter the destination."     Its doors are asymmetric as well, allowing for easy loading of passengers and cargo. In addition to the driver's side hatch, the passenger side features a power clamshell door that runs two-thirds the length of the vehicle.  A three-door hatch finishes the rear of the crossover.        Futuristic Interior     The futuristic theme and modern form language of the exterior carries through to the concept's interior.     "Through the materials, color palette and technology, the Ford Airstream Concept has distinct cues from the spacecraft and environments portrayed in 2001: A Space Odyssey," says Thomas.  "We're able to maximize the spaciousness of the interior, creating a lounge atmosphere in contrasting colors of cosmic red and white that provides an inviting experience for the ultimate journey."     The Ford Airstream Concept features a floating instrument panel with flush-mounted, touch-sensitive controls and a multi-function single gauge display provides the driver all primary information.     A Sharp(R) dual-view screen centrally mounted on the instrument panel provides a camera view and secondary driver-oriented information, while allowing the front-seat passenger to view DVDs and post mobile blogs.  The driver and front-seat passenger will navigate in style in modern, pod-shaped swiveling captain's chairs that also rotate so they can easily socialize.     In the rear, lounge-like seating is sculptural, creating a continuous cocoon-like environment wrapped in bold red B&B Italia fabric. The focal point of the rear seating area is a 360-degree screen for entertainment and games. The unique screen also creates ambient mood settings, including a modern lava lamp and virtual fire, as well as a live camera feed.        How the Rubber Meets the Road     The new HySeries Drive plug-in hydrogen fuel cell featured in the Ford Airstream Concept is more than a concept.     This powertrain is already on the road and driving in a Ford Edge prototype.  Ford scientists and engineers created this vehicle with partial funding from the United States Department of Energy.  The HySeries Drive delivers the combined city/highway equivalent fuel economy of 41 miles per gallon.     In this application, the fuel cell's sole function is to recharge the vehicle's lithium-ion battery pack as needed. This allows it to work like a portable generator, instead of an engine, as had been the case in previous Ford fuel cell vehicles.     The new fuel cell, supplied by Ford partner Ballard, operates in a steady state, allowing a significantly smaller, less expensive fuel cell and drastically improving the durability of the fuel cell.  With this system, the fuel cell delivers the power needed to recharge the lithium-ion batteries, rather than to be the primary power source to drive the wheels, as in a typical fuel cell-powered vehicle.     In pure electric mode, the Ford Airstream Concept can travel 25 miles before the fuel cell begins operating to recharge the vehicle's 336-volt lithium-ion battery pack.  With the hydrogen-powered fuel cell, the range increases another 280 miles for a total of 305 miles.        Safe Journeys     Safety belts remain the most important safety technology in vehicles. Ford is researching several new safety belt designs, including four-point safety belts found in the front seats of the Ford Airstream Concept.     "Inside, outside and under the hood, the Ford Airstream Concept speaks to the future," Mays said.  "Ford is looking out onto the horizon and imbuing crossovers with emotion, made even more powerful by our association with Airstream." Headline: Ford Chairman: 2007 Is Pivotal Year For Auto Maker
Story: By John D. Stoll   Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--Ford Motor Co. (F) Chairman Bill Ford Jr. on Sunday said 2007 is a "pivotal year" for the auto maker after a "difficult" 2006.   Ford, speaking during a press conference at the North American International Auto Show, said that his optimism for the company is unwavering and that his sole goal is to build a company that grows and prospers.   Ford lost about $7 billion in the first three quarters of 2006 as it continued to lose market share in the U.S. to more-nimble foreign competitors such as Toyota Motor Corp. (TM). Ford is in the midst of restructuring its North American operations and aims to restore profitability in the region by 2009.   Bill Ford, who stepped down as chief executive officer last September, said he's never enjoyed working with anyone as much as he has enjoyed working with new CEO Alan Mulally.   "We've laid the foundation for a stronger Ford," the company's chairman said.   Speaking at the same event, Mulally, a former Boeing Co. (BA) executive who is attending the Detroit auto show for the first time, said the auto maker is accelerating its product push in all the markets it competes in. He said Ford's domestic porfolio will include more crossover vehicles and small cars, and said the company will continue investing in its European luxury brands.   The executives were speaking at an event to introduce redesigned models and concept cars. At one point, Microsoft Corp. (MSFT) Chairman Bill Gates joined Mulally via videoconference. Microsoft and Ford said earlier Sunday they are teaming up on in-vehicle technology that will be available on Ford products later this year. Gates did not give details of the partnership, but said he looks forward to cultivating the partnership with Ford     -By John D. Stoll, Dow Jones Newswires; (313) 510 5002; john.stoll@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 11:55 ET (16:55 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: UK PRESS: Barclays' Business-banking Chief To Step Down
Story: LONDON (Dow Jones)--Peter Harvey will step down as chief executive of Barclays PLC's (BCS) U.K. business-banking operation, the Sunday Times reported without citing sources.   The report said that the move is part of a business-banking shakeup by Frits Seegers, who joined Barclays in July in the newly created role of CEO of global retail and commercial banking.   A senior Barclays executive has been lined up to take over from Harvey, the newspaper said. Harvey will continue to have a role in advising business-banking customers, although the exact position isn't clear, according to the report.     Newspaper Web site: http://www.timesonline.co.uk     -London Bureau, Dow Jones Newswires; +44 (0)20 7842 9320     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 07:37 ET (12:37 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: UK PRESS: Private Equity Groups Eye National Grid Unit
Story: LONDON (Dow Jones)--Private equity groups have approached National Grid PLC (NGG) about buying the company's broadcasting masts subsidiary before it is demerged, the Sunday Telegraph reported, without citing sources.   The subsidiary, National Grid Wireless, comprises the wireless business developed by both National Grid and Lattice, the gas distribution company, before their merger in 2003. It is expected to be valued at more than GBP2 billion, the report said.   National Grid Wireless has 14,500 sites, including phone masts used by T-Mobile and Vodafone PLC (VOD) and is part of the joint venture with television groups transmitting programs on Freeview digital satellite.   A proposed demerger from National Grid's core electricity and gas-transmission operations was announced in November.   Newspaper Web site: http://www.timesonline.co.uk   -London Bureau, Dow Jones Newswires; +44 (0)20 7842 9320     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 09:10 ET (14:10 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: BA Pension Deal Helps Fleet Plans, Buoys Suitors
Story: By Victoria Howley     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     LONDON (Dow Jones)--The pensions agreement between British Airways PLC (BAB) and its four main trade unions helps clear the way for the renewal of the carrier's long-haul fleet and makes the company more attractive as a takeover target, an analyst said Sunday.   British Airways said late Friday that it had reached consensus with the unions on a package of reforms to tackle a GBP2.1 billion deficit in its main pension scheme, New Airways Pension Scheme.   The carrier will make a one-off contribution of GBP800 million into the fund, and the annual contributions will be around GBP280 million for the next 10 years. A British Airways spokeswoman said that further details on the scheme would be released Monday.   The British Airways Forum, which represents the airline's four unions, is recommending the acceptance of the proposal and will now consult its members formally for approval of the scheme. Support from the unions is a major step forward for the carrier, which has been hit by industrial action in recent years.   "Resolution of the pensions issue would be a key milestone for British Airways," said John Strickland, director of JLS Consulting, which specializes in matters relating to the aviation industry. "The company would be able to get acceptable financial terms when ordering new aircraft."   British Airways is considering buying aircraft from Boeing (BA) and Airbus to upgrade its aging long-haul fleet. But the airline has said it won't order new long-haul airplanes until the pension deal is finalized, and its shares have been held back on the possibility of strike action over the pension issue.   Strickland said that agreement on pensions may also make British Airways more attractive to potential suitors. "BA is one of the best performers in the world among the legacy carriers," he said.   The U.K. carrier has been linked by analysts to Emirates Airline, as well as to private equity firms that might bid for BA in association with an airline company. Emirates has said it isn't currently pursuing acquisitions, however.   British Airways faces the prospect of disruption this year after the Transport & General Workers' Union said Dec. 15 that it would ballot some 11,000 cabin crew at the airline over possible strike action related to working conditions. That ballot is scheduled for Friday.   The union said the key issues in the dispute relate to the imposition of "practices without negotiation." Members have been angered by the management of sickness absence as well as the imposed abolition of some higher grades and lower rates for new starters, the union said.   Company Web site: http://www.ba.com   -By Victoria Howley, Dow Jones Newswires; 44 20 7842 9261; victoria.howley@dowjones.com   (Rod Stone contributed to this report.)     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 08:13 ET (13:13 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: : GE Money and Dixie Homecrafters Renew Agreement
Story: Revolving and Installment Consumer Credit Program Available  ST. PAUL, Minn.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--January 07, 2007--   GE Money's Sales Finance unit and Dixie Homecrafters, one of the fast-growing home improvement companies in America, today announced they have signed a five-year extension of their agreement to provide consumer financing.     Dixie Homecrafters, based in Chamblee, Ga., is the nation's second-largest home improvement company, selling and installing windows, siding, soffits and trim, and gutters for more than 17 years throughout the south.     GE Money - Sales Finance provides both revolving and installment financing to Dixie customers through its PROJECTLINE and PROJECTLOAN programs, and has funded more than $140 million in Dixie sales over the past several years. GE Money also offers Dixie customers a Dixie Homecrafters-branded credit card.     "Dixie is one of the premier home improvement companies in the country," said Bruce Christensen, vice president and general manager of home improvement for GE Money. "They understand that a strong consumer finance program adds value to their customers, and we're pleased to continue serving both Dixie and their customers."     Over the past 15 years, GE Money's Home Improvement division has been an industry leader, providing more than $13 billion in home improvement financing to more than half a million homeowners. Buyers can take advantage of GE's fast and easy application process, competitive interest rates, flexible financing options and knowledgeable customer service support.     "Our relationship with GE Money has been very good for us and our customers," said Jarryl Campbell, finance manager of Dixie Homecrafters. "They provide us with a fast, easy way to offer financing to our customers, their service is terrific and they've been an important part of helping Dixie succeed and grow."       ABOUT DIXIE HOMECRAFTERS     Since 1991, Dixie Homecrafters has set itself apart by adopting strict policies and procedures regarding homeowner satisfaction. Based in Chamblee, Ga., Dixie Homecrafters is the nation's second-largest home improvement company. The company sells and installs windows; siding; soffits, facia and trim; and gutters. Visit www.dixiehomecrafters.com to learn more.       ABOUT GE MONEY AND SALES FINANCE     Sales Finance, based in Kettering, Ohio, is part of GE Money, formerly GE Consumer Finance. The Sales Finance division provides private label credit card programs, marketing, installment lending and financial services for national and regional retailers, dealers, manufacturers and service providers in more than 20 industries including: home improvement, furniture, sporting goods, powersports, outdoor power equipment, automotive, recreational vehicles, consumer electronics and appliances, floor covering, marine, music, jewelry, and health care.     With $163 billion in assets, GE Money, a unit of General Electric Company (NYSE: GE), is a leading provider of credit services to consumers, retailers and auto dealers in approximately 50 countries around the world. GE Money, based in Stamford, Conn., offers a range of financial products, including private label credit cards, personal loans, bank cards, auto loans and leases, mortgages, corporate travel and purchasing cards, debt consolidation and home equity loans and credit insurance. More information can be found online at www.gemoney.com.     GE (NYSE: GE) is Imagination at Work -- a diversified technology, media and financial services company focused on solving some of the world's toughest problems. With products and services ranging from aircraft engines, power generation, water processing and security technology to medical imaging, business and consumer financing, media content and advanced materials, GE serves customers in more than 100 countries and employs more than 300,000 people worldwide. For more information, visit www.ge.com.       (C) 2007 General Electric Company, All rights reserved. Headline: : MediaFLO USA and FOX Bring News, Sports and Primetime Shows to Revolutionary Mobile Entertainment Service
Story: - World-class Content Line-up to Feature FOX Favorites Such as '24,' 'Prison Break,' 'FOX Report with Shepard Smith' and Original Online Sports Programming From FOXSports.com -       SAN DIEGO, Jan. 7 /PRNewswire-FirstCall/ -- MediaFLO(TM) USA Inc., a wholly owned subsidiary of QUALCOMM Incorporated (Nasdaq: QCOM), today announced a multi-year license agreement with Fox Mobile Entertainment and Fox Interactive Media that will bring programming from Twentieth Century Fox Television, Fox News Channel and FOX Sports Interactive to MediaFLO USA's revolutionary new mobile entertainment service.  MediaFLO USA intends to partner with wireless operators and top media companies to give consumers an unmatched mobile entertainment experience -- popular and engaging entertainment, news and sports viewed through a crystal-clear picture.     The deal adds a formidable array of FOX primetime and classic TV programs, such as "24," "Prison Break," "FOX Report with Shepard Smith" and "Your World with Neil Cavuto" to MediaFLO USA's compelling channel line-up.  FOX Sports on MSN, a unit of Fox Interactive Media, will also deliver several hours per day of original sports video programming that will be accessible to viewers via both MediaFLO USA and FOXSports.com.     "Fox Mobile Entertainment is proud to have led early mobile video efforts, offering a variety of popular FOX entertainment, sports and news programming to mobile users," said Lucy Hood, president of Fox Mobile Entertainment. "We're excited about the prospects of MediaFLO USA to improve the quality of mobile television and help us to engage consumers in new ways."     "Fox Mobile Entertainment, Fox Interactive Media and MediaFLO USA are combining to demonstrate the full potential of mobile media in what promises to be a breakthrough year in the delivery of mobile television services," said Paul Jacobs, chief executive officer, QUALCOMM.     "This agreement with MediaFLO USA marks a huge step forward for Fox Interactive Media as we continue to make content from our leading Web properties available on every possible platform," said Peter Levinsohn, president of Fox Interactive Media.     "MediaFLO USA will change the way people watch television," said Gina Lombardi, president of MediaFLO USA.  "This agreement with FOX ensures that consumers can enjoy some of the best loved programming on television, wherever and whenever they want, without compromising their viewing experience."     Guided by extensive market research and consumer trials, MediaFLO USA intends to secure familiar, premium content from many of the world's leading media companies and leverage its dedicated, nationwide multicast network to deliver live, full-length programming to mobile phones at TV quality.        About Fox Mobile Entertainment     Fox Mobile Entertainment is a leading provider of mobile content for wireless carriers and consumers, offering a variety of mobile products and services, such as downloadable wallpapers, screensavers, games and mobile video, including Mobisodes(R) Series, which leverage News Corporation's popular content and media brands.  Fox Mobile Entertainment's direct-to-consumer service allows billions of global mobile users to purchase from a huge selection of popular content from around the world, including branded content from News Corp. divisions; aggregated content from major media companies, including chart-topping ringtones from top music labels and mobile games from renowned game developers; and original content made exclusively for mobile phones by Fox Mobile Studios.  In September 2006, News Corp. (NYSE: NWS, NWS.A) and VeriSign announced a joint venture that combines Fox Mobile Entertainment's assets with Jamba.  The deal is expected to close soon.        About Fox Interactive Media     A division of News Corp. (NYSE: NWS), Fox Interactive Media (FIM) offers a global, border-free online network that caters to consumers by giving them the platform and tools to express themselves, communicate with each other, and engage with the best music, TV, film, sports, information and more.  The company's worldwide network includes such category leaders as MySpace, IGN Entertainment, FOXSports.com, RottenTomatoes, AskMen, AmericanIdol.com and more that together comprise one of the largest and most engaged audiences on the Web.        About Fox News Channel     FOX News Channel (FNC) is a 24-hour general news service covering breaking news as well as political, entertainment and business news.  For five years, FNC has been the most watched cable news channel in the nation and currently presents 10 out of the top 12 programs in cable news.  Owned by News Corp., FNC is available in more than 85 million homes.        About MediaFLO USA     MediaFLO USA Inc. aggregates and intends to deliver premium, TV-quality entertainment and information services to mobile phones over its dedicated nationwide wireless network.  Offering an unprecedented combination of full-length programming, short-format clips and realtime information and entertainment feeds, MediaFLO USA will deliver a uniquely compelling mobile viewing experience.  MediaFLO USA intends to partner with world-class content providers, wireless operators and advertisers to make its service available to U.S. consumers in the first quarter of 2007.  Based in San Diego, Calif., MediaFLO USA is a subsidiary of QUALCOMM Incorporated.     Except for the historical information contained herein, this news release contains forward-looking statements that are subject to risks and uncertainties, including the ability of MediaFLO USA to form timely and profitable partnerships with content providers, wireless operators and advertisers, the extent and speed to which FLO technology and the MediaFLO USA network are deployed, the extent and speed of adoption by consumers of MediaFLO USA's service, the speed with which Fox programming is integrated into the MediaFLO USA service package, change in economic conditions of the various markets MediaFLO USA serves, as well as the other risks detailed from time to time in QUALCOMM's SEC reports, including the report on Form 10-K for the year ended September 24, 2006, and most recent Form 10-Q.     QUALCOMM is a registered trademark of QUALCOMM Incorporated.  MediaFLO and FLO are trademarks of QUALCOMM Incorporated.  All other trademarks are the property of their respective owners.          QUALCOMM Contacts:      Julie Reynolds, MediaFLO USA Inc.      Phone:  1-858-845-3516      Email:  julier@qualcomm.com        Kristin Atkins, Corporate Communications      Phone:  1-858-845-5959      Email:  corpcomm@qualcomm.com        Garrett Ponder, Investor Relations      Phone:  1-858-658-4813      Email:  ir@qualcomm.com        Fox Mobile Entertainment Contact:      Lynne Hentemann      Phone:  1-310-598-4813      Email:  lynne.hentemann@fox.com      SOURCE  MediaFLO USA Inc.       /CONTACT: Julie Reynolds of MediaFLO USA Inc., +1-858-845-3516, julier@qualcomm.com; or Kristin Atkins, Corporate Communications, +1-858-845-5959, corpcomm@qualcomm.com, or Garrett Ponder, Investor Relations, +1-858-658-4813, ir@qualcomm.com, both of QUALCOMM Incorporated; or Lynne Hentemann of Fox Mobile Entertainment, +1-310-598-4813, lynne.hentemann@fox.com     Order free Annual Report for News Corporation  Visit http://djnewswires.ar.wilink.com/?link=NWS or call 1-888-301-0513  (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 16:00 ET (21:00 GMT)

Headline: Pioneer To Unveil New Plasma TV In US This Summer -Nikkei
Story: TOKYO (Nikkei)--Pioneer Corp. (6773.TO) will introduce a large-screen plasma television in the U.S. this summer, touting superior picture quality and high-definition compatibility, The Nikkei reported in its Monday edition.   The new plasma panel boasts a contrast ratio of better than 20,000-to-1, more than a six-fold improvement compared with existing plasma models and more than 15 times that of LCD panels. The screen is expected to measure 50-60 inches.   Pioneer initially planned to launch the TV leading up to the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics, but it decided to move up the date in light of faster-than-expected development. The product will be marketed in Japan and Europe within the year. The price and other details have yet to be determined.   Given that the panel can be made on existing production lines, the firm expects a smooth transition in shifting to the new model.   Pioneer only has a roughly 10% share of the global plasma TV market, despite a good reputation in the sector. By positioning the new plasma set as a core product and stressing its advanced functions, the company aims to both expand sales and stem price erosion.     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 12:58 ET (17:58 GMT)

Headline: GM Sweeps Car, Truck Awards At Detroit Auto Show
Story: By Jon Kamp     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--General Motors Corp. (GM) swept the car and truck of the year awards at the North American International Auto Show, beating out Japanese auto makers and rival Ford Motor Co. (F).   The awards, given Sunday, come just days after GM reported an unexpected slide in U.S. sales for December, fueled in part by lower sales of light trucks.   The awards, voted on by journalists, also represented a turnaround from last year, when Honda Motor Co. (HMC) swept the categories.   The Chevrolet Silverado was named 2007 truck of the year, while the Saturn Aura was named the year's top car. The Silverado topped the Ford Edge and the Mazda CX7, while the Aura topped the Honda Fit and Toyota Motor Corp.'s (TM) Camry.   Ed Peper, Chevrolet's general manager, called the award a "very encouraging" validation for the GM brand.   GM, the largest auto maker in the U.S., is restructuring its operations after posting big financial losses in recent years as it struggled to sustain market share in the U.S. and to rein in costs.   GM, like its main domestic competitors, has struggled in part because of declining sales of highly profitable trucks and SUVs amid high gasoline prices and shifting demographics.   Sales of the Silverado, for instance, were down 10% in 2006 from the previous year at about 636,000 vehicles. In December alone, Silverado sales were off 20%.     -By Jon Kamp, Dow Jones Newswires; 312-750-4129; jon.kamp@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 10:33 ET (15:33 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: UPDATE: New Minivans May Be Big Opportunity For Chrysler
Story: (Updates with comments from Chief Executive Tom LaSorda in paragraphs four, 10 and 12.)       By Terry Kosdrosky     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--The Chrysler Group's launch of its redesigned minivans this year - complete with the latest seating innovation and a new exterior look - comes as its U.S. competitors pull out of the segment, developments that could aid the struggling auto maker's turnaround.   The U.S. unit of DaimlerChrysler AG (DCX) invented the minivan in the mid-1980s and has been a market leader since. But it has faced stiff competition from Honda Motor Co.'s (HMC) Odyssey and Toyota Motor Corp.'s (TM) Sienna in recent years. All have spent time and money one-upping each other with new innovations, such as fold-flat third row seats, a split third row that folds flat and fold-flat second-row seats.   The 2008 Chrysler Town & Country and Dodge Grand Caravan will be revealed at the North American International Auto show and go on sale in the fall. They have the requisite "gee-whiz" interior innovation - second-row seats that turn 180 degrees to face the third row, with a removable table in between. That's known as "Swivel 'n Go," which builds on Chrysler's "Stow 'n Go."   Chrysler Group Chief Executive Tom LaSorda said Sunday after the minivan introduction that he expects "at least" 25% to 40% of buyers to take the Swivel 'n Go option.   Chrysler also makes an exterior statement with the 2008 model, scrapping the egg shape for a more linear, "athletic" appearance, said Chrysler design chief Trevor Creed.   With Ford Motor Co. (F) and General Motors Corp. (GM) essentially pulling out of the traditional minivan segment, Chrysler has a golden opportunity with its new model, said Erich Merkle, director of forecasting at IRN Inc. in Grand Rapids, Mich.   "This is huge for Chrysler," he said. "They've always been kind of the front-runner in the minivan segment. That fact that GM and Ford are exiting and they have a new product, that leaves all the more for Chrysler."   Merkle said it will be difficult for Honda and Toyota to fill the gap left by Ford and GM as quickly because of their capacity constraints.   He called Chrysler's minivans one of the most important vehicles of the show.   LaSorda said Sunday on the sidelines of the auto show that he's "kind of happy" that GM and Ford have pulled out of the segment. He said the minivan continues to be a "bread and butter" product for Chrysler and sees the overall minivan market at 1.1 million a year.   Chrysler minivan sales slumped in 2006, with the Town & Country off 12% and the Caravan off 7%. Toyota Sienna sales were up 1.5% and Honda Odyssey sales were up 2.4%.   LaSorda said he expects the new minivans to bring Chrysler's minivan sales back up above 400,000. Chrysler sold 370,245 minivans last year. He also said Chrysler wouldn't sell as many minivans to fleet customers, such as car rental companies, since they will be fresh products.   The minivan sales decline was indicative of a general weakening in Chrysler's performance last year. The company's inventory bulged and it had to cut production and offer big incentives on its pickup trucks and SUVs.   Chrysler, which lost market share despite launching 10 new products, reported a $1.5 billion third-quarter loss. A turnaround plan is expected to be revealed next month.   Merkle said the second half of this year "should look a lot better" for Chrysler in part because of the minivans, which carry good profit margins.   He said Chrysler made the right move changing the exterior, which can carry risks.   "That's one of the things I've been looking for," Merkle said. "It speaks volumes about Chrysler's willingness to take risks. They're taking their No. 1 vehicle, their top selling vehicle, and saying they're going to shake it up. When you get your top vehicle, people tend to get very cautious. That doesn't seem to be the route Chrysler is going to be taking."   The minivans also offer other interior goodies, such as pinpoint LED lighting, retractable sun shades, one-touch power third-row folding seats and ambient halo lighting.   The Chrysler Town & Country will come in three trim levels, LX, Touring and Country Limited while the Dodge Grand Caravan will come in the SE and SXT levels.   The vans come with three powertrain options. A 3.3-liter, flex-fuel V-6 engine with a four-speed transmission or a 3.8-liter or 4.0-liter V-6 engine with a six-speed transmission.   Side-curtain airbags covering all rows are standard, as is an electronic stability program.   Creed said Chrysler "took every feature on every minivan today that we don't have that they do, and added some of our own features."   -By Terry Kosdrosky, Dow Jones Newswires; (313) 226-1251; terry.kosdrosky@dowjones.com     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 12:37 ET (17:37 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.

Headline: : Chevrolet Volt - GM's Concept Electric Vehicle - Could Nearly Eliminate Trips to the Gas Station
Story: DETROIT, Jan. 7 /PRNewswire/ -- The Chevrolet Volt concept sedan, powered by the E-flex System - GM's next-generation electric propulsion system - could nearly eliminate trips to the gas station.     The Chevrolet Volt is a battery-powered, four-passenger electric vehicle that uses a gas engine to create additional electricity to extend its range. The Volt draws from GM's previous experience in starting the modern electric vehicle market when it launched the EV1 in 1996, according to GM Vice Chairman Robert A. Lutz.     "The EV1 was the benchmark in battery technology and was a tremendous achievement," Lutz said. "Even so, electric vehicles, in general, had limitations. They had limited range, limited room for passengers or luggage, couldn't climb a hill or run the air conditioning without depleting the battery, and had no device to get you home when the battery's charge ran low.     "The Chevrolet Volt is a new type of electric vehicle. It addresses the range problem and has room for passengers and their stuff. You can climb a hill or turn on the air conditioning and not worry about it."     The Volt can be fully charged by plugging it into a 110-volt outlet for approximately six hours a day. When the lithium-ion battery is fully charged, the Volt can deliver 40 city miles of pure electric vehicle range. When the battery is depleted, a 1L, three-cylinder turbocharged engine spins at a constant speed, or revolutions per minute (rpm), to create electricity and replenish the battery. According to Lutz, this increases the fuel economy and range.     "If you lived within 30 miles from work (60 miles round trip) and charged your vehicle every night when you came home or during the day at work, you would get 150 miles per gallon," Lutz said. "More than half of all Americans live within 20 miles of where they work (40 miles round trip). In that case, you might never burn a drop of gas during the life of the car."     In addition, the Chevrolet Volt is designed to run on E85, a fuel blend of 85 percent ethanol and 15 percent gasoline. Using E85, fuel economy of 150 mpg would translate into more than 525 miles per petroleum gallon.     In the event a driver forgets to charge the vehicle or goes on a vacation far away, the Volt would still get 50 mpg by using the engine to convert gasoline into electricity and extending its range up to 640 miles, more than double that of today's conventional vehicles.     A technological breakthrough required to make this concept a reality is a large lithium-ion battery. This type of electric car, which the technical community calls an "EV range-extender," would require a battery pack that weighs nearly 400 pounds (181 kg). Some experts predict that such a battery - or a similar battery - could be production-ready by 2010 to 2012.     Jon Lauckner, GM vice president of Global Program Management, said the Volt is uniquely built to accommodate a number of advanced technology propulsion solutions that can give GM a competitive advantage.     "Today's vehicles were designed around mechanical propulsion systems that use petroleum as their primary source of fuel." Lauckner said. Tomorrow's vehicles need to be developed around a new propulsion architecture with electricity in mind. The Volt is the first vehicle designed around GM's E-flex System.     "That's why we are also showing a variant of the Chevrolet Volt with a hydrogen-powered fuel cell, instead of a gasoline engine EV range-extender," said Lauckner. "Or, you might have a diesel engine driving the generator to create electricity, using bio-diesel. Finally, an engine using 100-percent ethanol might be factored into the mix. The point is, all of these alternatives are possible with the E-Flex System."     The Volt concept car is built on a modified future architecture, Lauckner said, similar to the one GM uses for current small cars, such as the Chevrolet Cobalt and HHR.     According to Larry Burns, GM vice president for research and development and strategic planning, the world's growing demand for energy and its dependence on oil for transportation is the common theme behind today's headlines.     "Whether your concern is energy security, global climate change, natural disasters, the high price of gas, the volatile pricing of a barrel of oil and the effect that unpredictability has on Wall Street - all of these issues point to a need for energy diversity," said Burns. "Today, there are more than 800 million cars and trucks in the world. In 15 years, that will grow to 1.1 billion vehicles. We can't continue to be 98-percent dependent on oil to meet our transportation needs. Something has to give. We think the Chevrolet Volt helps bring about the diversity that is needed. If electricity met only 10 percent of the world's transportation needs, the impact would be huge."        GM's E-flex System moves automobile toward new electric age     GM's E-flex System enables multiple propulsion systems to fit into a common chassis, using electric drive to help the world diversify energy sources and establish electricity from the grid as one of those sources.     "The DNA of the automobile has not changed in more than 100 years," said Burns. "Vehicles still operate in pretty much the same fashion as when Karl Benz introduced the 'horseless carriage' in 1886.     "While mechanical propulsion will be with us for many decades to come, GM sees a market for various forms of electric vehicles, including fuel cells and electric vehicles using gas and diesel engines to extend the range. With our new E-flex concept, we can produce electricity from gasoline, ethanol, bio- diesel or hydrogen.     "We can tailor the propulsion to meet the specific needs and infrastructure of a given market. For example, somebody in Brazil might use 100-percent ethanol (E100) to power an engine generator and battery. A customer in Shanghai might get hydrogen from the sun and create electricity in a fuel cell. Meanwhile, a customer in Sweden might use wood to create bio- diesel."     The Chevrolet Volt is just the first variant of the E-flex System. The Volt uses a large battery and a small, 1L turbocharged gasoline engine to produce enough electricity to go up to 640 miles and provide triple-digit fuel economy. GM will show other variations of the propulsion systems at future auto shows.     "GM is building a fuel cell variant that mirrors the propulsion system in the Chevrolet Sequel (fuel cell concept)," Burns said. "Instead of a big battery and a small engine generator used in the Volt, we would use a fuel cell propulsion system with a small battery to capture energy when the vehicle brakes. Because the Volt is so small and lightweight, we would need only about half of the hydrogen storage as the Sequel to get 300 miles of range."        Future concepts might incorporate diesel generators, bio-diesel and E-100.        Environmentally conscious vehicles can be aesthetically appealing       With exterior proportions associated more with classic sports cars, the Chevrolet Volt conveys an immediate message of agility and sophistication. Twenty-one-inch wheels and sheer, taut surface relationships reiterate the statement. The Volt's athletic design challenges the notion that an environmentally conscious vehicle can't be beautiful and possess an aesthetic spirit that matches its driving characteristics.     "We leveraged our resources around the globe to develop the design aesthetic for the Volt," said Ed Welburn, vice president, GM Global Design. "It was important that the design capture the face of the Chevrolet as it's recognized around the world."     True to the heritage of its Chevrolet bowtie, the Volt's exterior design suggests spirited performance and is wrapped in a stylish package, with classic Chevrolet performance cues that hint at both Camaro and Corvette. On the inside, near-term technologies and innovative materials combine with ingenious use of ambient light for an interior environment that's light, airy and thoughtful.     "First and foremost, this is an advanced technology vehicle that uses little to no fuel at all. But we didn't see any reason why that should compromise its design," said Anne Asensio, executive director, GM Design. Asensio led the design team that created the Volt concept, with designs solicited from GM's studios around the world.     "We wanted a size that connected with everyone, so we designed a small car," said Asensio. "In the end, the interior design team from England inspired the final interior execution, and the exterior is the work of the Michigan advanced design team.     "Our job was to design a vehicle people could easily imagine," said Asensio. "It couldn't be a 'science project,' because that's not what this car is all about. It had to be realistic, executable and carry the essence of the Chevrolet brand." Headline: ITALIAN PRESS: Autostrade Plans EUR1.2B Invest In '07
Story: MILAN (Dow Jones)--Autostrade SpA (AUTO.MI) plans to invest EUR1.2 billion in Italy's roads network in 2007, business daily Il Sole 24 Ore reported Sunday, citing the highway operator's Chief Executive Giovanni Castellucci.   Italian government concerns over road investment in Italy contributed to Autostrade and Spanish highways operator Abertis Infraestructuras SA's (ABE.MC) decision last month to shelve an agreed merger.   Italian Infrastructure Minister Antonio Di Pietro welcomed the investment pledge, and urged European Commission officials to drop ongoing investigations into Rome's role in the Autostrade-Abertis merger being abandoned, Il Sole 24 Ore reported.     Newspaper Web site: http://www.ilsole24ore.com     -By Milan Bureau, Dow Jones Newswires, +39-02-5821 9901     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 15:50 ET (20:50 GMT)

Story: Edited by Paul Vigna     Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     (call: 201-938-5172; email: paul.vigna@dowjones.com)   AUTO SHOW MARKET TALK can be found using N/DJMT and I/AUT   10:53 (Dow Jones) The media are descending on Detroit. Headline: UPDATE: Ford Chairman Says 2007 Is Pivotal Year For Co
Story: (Adds comments from CEO on partnerships and comments from Ford Americas chief.)        By John D. Stoll      Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES     DETROIT (Dow Jones)--Ford Motor Co. (F) Chairman Bill Ford Jr. on Sunday said 2007 is a "pivotal year" for the auto maker after a "difficult" 2006.   Ford, speaking during a press conference at the North American International Auto Show, said that his optimism for the company is unwavering and that his sole goal is to build a company that grows and prospers.   Ford lost about $7 billion in the first three quarters of 2006 as it continued to lose market share in the U.S. to more-nimble foreign competitors such as Toyota Motor Corp. (TM). Ford is in the midst of restructuring its North American operations and aims to restore profitability in the region by 2009.   Bill Ford, who stepped down as chief executive officer last September, said he's never enjoyed working with anyone as much as he has enjoyed working with new CEO Alan Mulally.   "We've laid the foundation for a stronger Ford," the company's chairman said.   Speaking at the same event, Mulally, a former Boeing Co. (BA) executive who is attending the Detroit auto show for the first time, said the auto maker is accelerating its product push in all the markets it competes in. He said Ford's domestic portfolio will include more crossover vehicles and small cars, and said the company will continue investing in its European luxury brands.   Mulally, speaking with reporters after the press conference, said that he expects more collaborative alliances to spring up in the global auto industry and said the auto maker will continue collaborating with Toyota.   He downplayed, however, a recent meeting he had with the chairman of Toyota. Mulally said Ford has a variety of collaborations, but he ruled out a broad alliance with the Japanese company.   Mulally noted that partnerships have worked in the airline industry and that he expects "more alliances working around the world" in the auto business. "It benefits everybody," he said.   At one point during Sunday's Ford event to introduce redesigned models and concept cars, Microsoft Corp. (MSFT) Chairman Bill Gates joined Mulally via videoconference. Microsoft and Ford said earlier Sunday they are teaming up on in-vehicle technology that will be available on Ford products later this year. Gates did not give details of the partnership, but said he looks forward to cultivating the relationship with Ford.   Ford in recent months has accelerated its North American turnaround plan, which was first unveiled last January.   Mark Fields, Ford's Americas chief and the architect of the restructuring strategy, told reporters on Sunday that he expects U.S. light-vehicle sales to be down slightly in 2007. He also noted that job growth is expected to moderate and the housing market is expected to remain weak, which could affect light truck sales.   Fields said he expects sales of F-Series pickup trucks - Ford's top-selling vehicle - to continue their current trend through the first half of the year. F-Series sales fell 12% to just under 800,000 vehicles in 2006, well short of the company's target of 900,000.   Fields added that Ford will do enough on incentives to keep their dealers "competitive," but that the incentives won't be excessive.     -By John D. Stoll, Dow Jones Newswires; (313) 510 5002; john.stoll@dowjones.com   (Paul Vigna contributed to this article)     (END) Dow Jones Newswires  January 07, 2007 13:36 ET (18:36 GMT)  Copyright (c) 2007 Dow Jones & Company, Inc.
